{"Author": "AH", "Date": "on January 14, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works well.", "Text": "So many reviews, what more can be said. This hobby is addictive and can get expensive, but is very fun."}
{"Author": "Jim F.", "Date": "on January 14, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I really enjoy this hub", "Text": "I really enjoy this hub. It's very versatile, comparable with so many devices and I cannot say enough good things about their customer service. It's great! You will not be disappointed!"}
{"Author": "T. Ott", "Date": "on January 14, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "An Excellent Choice for the Internet of Things (IoT)", "Text": "So, far -- so excellent!\n\nI am glad I chose Samsung over the other brand hubs for the IoT devices in my home. The deciding factor was the hub's ability to communicate with BOTH Z-Wave and Zigbee. Although I definitely prefer Z-Wave protocol, it is reassuring to have a device that will work well with Zigbee devices in the event I need a specialized IoT device that is not available in the Z-Wave protocol.\n\nAs of today's date, I've used this product for about 90 days, and there have been no material, workmanship or operational issues."}
{"Author": "Muhammad", "Date": "on January 14, 2018", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Three Stars", "Text": "It has compatibility issues with brands like yeelight, which I want to use."}
{"Author": "Philthy G", "Date": "on January 13, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Like having the Force or a Butler around the house", "Text": "Philthy reviews... The device that turns on his house lights when it's pitch black and the switch is on other side of room\n\nPhilthy cuts to the chase....and says Click to buy to have Alexa start controlling more than ordering Doritos or playing MC Hammer..I mean NSYNC...no I mean Miley...wait Maroon 5...that's it.\n\nThis is a hub. That means it's the brains but not the limbs. You need other things to control the lights etc. As a hub you have many other choices like Wink or Amazon but I opted for Samsung. Brand loyalty I guess. But coupled with the switch it works wonders. Next up is a thermometer."}
{"Author": "Glenn Harris", "Date": "on January 13, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Do NOT buy", "Text": "Incompetent support. Horid product. I wasted too much time and money on the hub and related devices."}
{"Author": "GV", "Date": "on January 12, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "A must if you automating home with smartthings"}
{"Author": "Wm. R Henninger", "Date": "on January 12, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Amazing device and a lot of fun. No end to what you can do."}
{"Author": "John T. McClanaghan", "Date": "on January 12, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easy to get into home automation with this hub.", "Text": "Sets up fairly easily and controls a whole lot of other devices. Integrates with Amazon Alexa well also."}
{"Author": "William Gracia", "Date": "on January 12, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Works day in and day out with no reliability issues so far. 2 months in service so far."}
{"Author": "Ed", "Date": "on January 12, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Limited", "Text": "Limited products supported. Sold with my Echo show, but it is not compatible with Alexa. Gave it away, couldn't find any one to buy it."}
{"Author": "Matthew K.", "Date": "on January 12, 2018", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Got it but don\u2019t really use it. I have ...", "Text": "Got it but don\u2019t really use it. I have the hue bridge doing what I already need to be done."}
{"Author": "K. M. Senger", "Date": "on January 12, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "so far this has been a great replacement with zero", "Text": "Purchased to replace the wink home hub v.1 which was awful....so far this has been a great replacement with zero issues"}
{"Author": "Jim Redington", "Date": "on January 12, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "... did integrate my cameras to it and that was easy.", "Text": "Have not really put it to test yet but did integrate my cameras to it and that was easy."}
{"Author": "Ayla Blu", "Date": "on January 12, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "GREAT CHOICE - easy to set up and use - grows with your Smart additions", "Text": "JUST installed and haven't fully explored all the potential yet, but so far so good! After a lot of research on how best to about bringing our home into the \"smart\" direction, and realizing that we would need some sort of 'hub' to accomplish what we wanted to do (voice commands for everything via Echo) this was the \"Smart\" choice.\n\nEasy set up, and easy to use, even for newbies to the smart stuff, like me, who tend to not be the brightest when it comes to technology.\n\nAs homes are trending towards this technology, and more and more products become available AND affordable, the Samsung SmartThings Hub will be able to handle it. It will grow with the addition of other smart additions we plan on making down the road (door locks, security system).. and enhances our existing Echo products even further by optimizing voice commands to include our new smart lighting and smart thermostat, as well as our existing smart TV's.\n\nSmall and white - so will blend in with most home d\u00e9cor and not be obvious. It is required to be hooked up to your modem, so take that into consideration. Comes with all cords needed and easy to follow instructions."}
{"Author": "Terrell Evans", "Date": "on January 11, 2018", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Cool product. But had to learn patience", "Text": "Cool product . But had to learn patience."}
{"Author": "Erin", "Date": "on January 11, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Excellent Support", "Text": "I recently migrated from ADT Pulse to SmartThings for all my home automation needs. SmartThings allows for more integration of products and has so many more standard features. The great part is that you have an active community to ask questions and get help when stuck with a problem."}
{"Author": "Gosumec", "Date": "on January 11, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works like a charm", "Text": "Samsung makes high quality products. This is one example. Works like a charm"}
{"Author": "Peter Oconnor", "Date": "on January 10, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "great buy and happy to give the gift of a ...", "Text": "Works very well, great buy and happy to give the gift of a Smart Home."}
{"Author": "rees*pieces", "Date": "on January 9, 2018", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Device still needs major improvement.", "Text": "Like the device but a outage that lasted for several days caused by Samsung problems has tarnished my opinion. For something that wants to serve as a Hub for a myriad of devices, it has to be more reliable."}
{"Author": "V. Drady", "Date": "on January 8, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great product.", "Text": "Works exactly as described. Hue lights, micro switch for fan and ecobee thermostat all work from phone, tablet and echo/Alexa. Looking forward for my next \"thing\"."}
{"Author": "Ritchie Scott", "Date": "on January 8, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "simple set up and compatible with a wide range of smart home products", "Text": "Arrived quickly, simple set up and compatible with a wide range of smart home products."}
{"Author": "Adrian Visan", "Date": "on January 8, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "... have bought this hub for home automation and works great, I can do a lot of scenes using ...", "Text": "I have bought this hub for home automation and works great, I can do a lot of scenes using the linked devices."}
