{"Author": "C. Melin", "Date": "on January 7, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works great, easily links to the various smart devices I ...", "Text": "Works great, easily links to the various smart devices I have. I think all of the device I have attached are Zwave so far, bu they work great."}
{"Author": "Amazon Addict!", "Date": "on January 6, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "This hub recognizes both the Samsung lights as well as ...", "Text": "This hub recognizes both the Samsung lights as well as the Sengled lights and also picked up all of the Hue bulbs connected to my Hue hub."}
{"Author": "Tortuga", "Date": "on January 5, 2018", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Endless Customization, Home Automation at its Best!", "Text": "The hub was a snap to setup, and works with all of my smart home gadgets. My Schlage lock isn't compatible with the hub for lock codes, but that is what introduced me to the wonder of the SmartThings forums. There are custom apps and device handlers for almost anything! Not only did I get my lock setup, complete with logging/code creation/burner codes/etc, but I was able to setup a Raspberry Pi relay to open/close my garage right from the SmartThings app. The customization ability is really endless! My only knock on the hub is that some of my devices show up as \"unavailable\" in the app from time to time. Typically this happens to my wifi smart plugs, and it's not terribly frequent."}
{"Author": "Velocity", "Date": "on January 5, 2018", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Good, still quirky", "Text": "I've used a few different home automation hubs including older models of Smarrtthings and all of them are quirky. Smartthings is quirky as well, but the latest model is less quirky than others. It looks like since Samsung took over there is less user created content which is disappointing. In terms of what is out there now, Smarrtthings is the tops and best in my opinion. None are perfect, they all still seem to be evolving. The zigbee and zwave are becoming more standardized which will help quite a bit. In my opinion, there isn't a home automation hub on the market today that is without quirks, Smartthings makes it more livable and functional though."}
{"Author": "Bethanne D.", "Date": "on January 4, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Terribly unreliable, wast of time tech", "Text": "I can guarantee these things wont be around long. Terribly unreliable, wast of time tech. Constant errors, disconnects, delays... Save your money and wait 'till something reliable comes along as it always does.\n\nSee reviews below if you need more convincing..."}
{"Author": "whbatista", "Date": "on January 4, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "excelent"}
{"Author": "R. Broder", "Date": "on January 4, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Let me start the review by saying I have worked ...", "Text": "Let me start the review by saying I have worked in IT for the last 30 years. I've had the Smartthings Hub v2 since April, 2017. Although it seemed to work most of the time, there have been intermittent problems with devices going off-line, being unavailable and having incorrect status displayed in the app.\n\nTonight I am, despite restarting the hub, restarting my network infrastructure (i.e. routers, switches etc.), unable to control my devices.\n\nI'm done. This was supposed to make things easier. Instead it has been a total exercise in frustration."}
{"Author": "Elie", "Date": "on January 4, 2018", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Best of Smartthings products", "Text": "Always ON even if there is no internet for a while. It take around 2 seconds to go online."}
{"Author": "G. Stark", "Date": "on January 3, 2018", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Do not buy if firmware not updated", "Text": "Returned because a firmware update broke interconnection between Samsung TV (I have a 8000 series). Samsung knows about it since fall and no fix yet."}
{"Author": "Martin Pare", "Date": "on January 3, 2018", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love it, was using a Vera Plus", "Text": "Love it, was using a Vera Plus, was having loads of issue with it... But since i've switched to Smartthings, everything is working great, a bit of a learning curve to program my scenes.... Would be nice if Samsung would do an web user interface not just the api...."}
{"Author": "Tthai", "Date": "on January 2, 2018", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Work great as my 2nd one", "Text": "Work great as my 2nd one. However, there will be some mysteries or conspiracies of why it will stop functioning completely after few years of operation. It seems to me a control server having capability of switching off if I upgrade the firmware several times. None of the ICs was damage but it will reject to operate as usual."}
{"Author": "Kevin from Boston", "Date": "on January 2, 2018", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Good if you have existing smart devices requiring a central hub.", "Text": "I have several Z-wave devices and got a Z-wave compatible door lock so I decided to purchase the hub. For me, it works great. If I were looking to purchase, I would ask myself whether this is the way to proceed. It seem like the cheaper devices now being marketed do no require the hub and are not compatible with the hub. If I had to guess, the future is hub-less, with the competition being which technology/app will win out. I don't have high expectations for the longevity of Z-wave and similar technologies."}
{"Author": "huckw", "Date": "on January 2, 2018", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Pretty good....RBoy smart apps makes it better!", "Text": "I originally had some issues getting the hub to connect (got the flashing blue light) and stay connected to my network but after a phone call to customer support we got it working. But, this was not plug and play for me so I take a 1/2 star for that. I only have a single device currently, the Schlage BE469 lock. This paired immediately and gave me basic control...but who wants just basic control when you can have it ALL? Not me!!\nActually the whole point of the lock and hub for me was to manage a remote lock at our vacation rental 90 miles away....so I needed a way to manage the lock from afar. It *seems* like there are two options for this (its confusing on the ST forums so I might be wrong)....but the RBoy name kept popping up. So I shelled out the $35 for a lifetime supply of RBoy apps, followed their instructions for installing the Smart App lock manager and device handler and absolutely LOVE it.\nThe only thing I'll take another 1/2 star for is that ST does not yet allow the smart apps to do local processing....come on Samsung, this is HUGE!! So the RBoy lock manager let's me set a code that begins working at 3:00 on some date and expires after 12:00 noon on a later day, which is SUPER cool....and it works....as long as you have internet at those specific times/dates. I know you need internet to set up the schedule, but it should be allowed to store that on the hub and then execute locally without need for internet. Even if it could pre-fetch 24-48 hours worth of scheduled tasks would give me a little peace of mind."}
{"Author": "KFMP", "Date": "on January 2, 2018", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "If SmartThings would do a better job at integrating WiFi devices I would absolutely love ...", "Text": "If SmartThings would do a better job at integrating WiFi devices I would absolutely love it. As it stands it is very lacking in that department, but it is still a solid device."}
{"Author": "M.J.", "Date": "on January 1, 2018", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Smart things was too inconsistent", "Text": "I sent it back. I\u2019ll try again in a couple years and hope that they or some other company have addressed the bugs and disconnection issues.\nMy wemo switches, working through my phone app, have been bulletproof so far. Smart things was too inconsistent."}
{"Author": "Rodney", "Date": "on December 31, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "and reset by removing powe Ethernet chord and batteries several times looks like junk so", "Text": "Initially no luck with setup. Two hours in and still have a blinking blue light. Changed out ethernet chord, reset with red button several times, and reset by removing power Ethernet chord and batteries several times looks like junk so far"}
{"Author": "engineering_enthusiast", "Date": "on December 31, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easy setup, great functionality", "Text": "We wanted to add lighting automation to our home.\n\nSetup: This product is exceptionally easy to setup. Setup was under 10 minutes, probably closer to 5. I almost always pre-read instruction manuals, but in this case I didn\u2019t use/need them.\n\nThe App: The SmartThings app is easy to use. We control it with any of 3 iOS devices (attempting Kindle now) and control a number of lights throughout our home. The automation triggers are menu driven and easy to configure/customize.\n\nOther niceties: Automation has replaced our old box timers, which were ancient and on their way out anyway. The power metering feature is handy; no more scrambling for my tried and true Kill-a-watt meter if I\u2019m curious how much power a device is using."}
{"Author": "Ron Texas", "Date": "on December 30, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Hubs and Decisions and Choices", "Text": "How did I ever survive without this marvel of technology and all its connections to THINGS in my daily life. There are several choices of \"hub\" to connect appliances, switches, lights, thermostats, etc to help with the daily \"things\" in your life and to give comfort and a sense of security to ones life. While working on my Ph.D. degree more than thirty-five years ago, I was taught and learned the skills necessary to research the world around me. At that time, it was intended to further the publishing credentials for a college teaching job, tenure and all the academic lauding attended to higher education. The skills have served me well since graduate school and applied to many mundane subjects like \"hubs\" for connection of electronic. Samsung has developed along with others the technology to put z waves, a part of the spectrum of radio wave to practical use for security, comfort and reliability of functional things and appliance in one's home. I made a decision on Samsung's technology and expertise that I have not regretted in the last few months."}
{"Author": "Geocaching", "Date": "on December 30, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Works great"}
{"Author": "perfectstroker", "Date": "on December 30, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Does not allow alternate control by device-specific remote", "Text": "The SmartThings Hub (mine's a V2) is supposed to consolidate control of several wireless protocols into one interface, but it will not allow alternate control with a device-specific remote. I intended to control Z-link outdoor security lighting with it (8 separate switches), but my wife also needed to be able to control the same security lighting, and she does not use computers. So, at the same time I purchased the SmartThings Hub, I purchased a GE Z-link controller for her, and set it up to control the security lighting. After a few repeated failures to connect the SmartThings Hub to my security lighting, I learned from SmartThings tech support that the Hub cannot be configured for alternate control (i.e., control by either the SmartThings Hub or the GE Z-link remote, alternately), so I have never used it. I left it connected to my network until last week, to keep up the updates, but finally decided it would be of better use as an expensive paperweight. The inability to accommodate alternate control should have been prominently addressed in the product's advertising."}
{"Author": "Josh", "Date": "on December 30, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Really simple to set up and I forget it's even ...", "Text": "Really simple to set up and I forget it's even there. Would have gave five stars but it's the only hub I've had any experience with."}
{"Author": "Dr. Bohannon", "Date": "on December 30, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Versatile, but goes off randomly. Requires hard connection ...", "Text": "Versatile, but goes off randomly. Requires hard connection to modem, but suffers from WiFi interference. But a very long lan cable to help,with this. Made a huge diff for me."}
{"Author": "C. Barret", "Date": "on December 29, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Not ready for non-geeks.", "Text": "This simply isn't a technology that is ready for prime time. I have had my hub fail 3 times, requiring a full reset and a re-registration of all 13 of my devices on the system. This is a system that is more of a pain than pleasure. Sure, its great I can adjust my thermostat from afar, but the fact that I have spent nearly 20 hours maintaining it negates any benefit.\nIts not like I dont know what I am doing, I have been messing with home automation since the X10 days. I just thought I would be getting a headache free tool and what I got was another pile of annoyances."}
{"Author": "CJ", "Date": "on December 29, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works great with Zigbee and Z-Wave products, good price and support.", "Text": "Works great with Zigbee and Z-Wave products. Simple to set up and have had no issues with it. Added bonus that I got it on a holiday sale. Some products like Echo Plus or Almond come with a built-in hub, but I prefer to have a separate unit."}
{"Author": "riboflvn", "Date": "on December 29, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Nice. Easy to install and it found all other ...", "Text": "Nice. Easy to install and it found all other automation items including Schlage locks and Hue bulbs."}
{"Author": "Bill hammer", "Date": "on December 29, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "TOTAL TRASH CONSTANTLY DOWN. JUNK", "Text": "I purchased this JUNK they constantly update because of bugs. Every time they do you have to re set whole house. Many calls n emails to no avail although their tech support tries to remedy fast nothing works. JUNK DONT BUY. Junk junk junk junk junk junk junk"}
{"Author": "Danny Lopez", "Date": "on December 29, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Hardware works well. Wish the app was a little ...", "Text": "Hardware works well. Wish the app was a little more user friendly."}
{"Author": "Somtr", "Date": "on December 28, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Hardware is as good as a brick", "Text": "Received as a gift. App doesn't allow me to login on an Android. Hardware is as good as a brick."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on December 28, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "it's a SmartThings :)"}
{"Author": "Brenna", "Date": "on December 28, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "He used it to sync all his other smart devices together to complete his smart home", "Text": "I bought this for my 28 year old brother for christmas. He used it to sync all his other smart devices together to complete his smart home. It was a great price! Very happy with this purchase."}
{"Author": "Max", "Date": "on December 28, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Totally recommended", "Text": "OK, I bought this on a whim with no intention to pursue home automation. The wife acceptance factor (WAF) is important to me, so I did not want to get involved with anything that would overwhelm her day-to-day. That said, this has really made our lives easier. It is fun automating simple things like lights, and keeping track of when we come and go. Overall, I have been having a lot of fun with this device, and am glad I took the plunge. As a cyber security guy, there are certain things I won't explore (e.g. smart home locks, smart home assistants) on general principle, but for what I have pursued, I feel that it has made me more aware of the goings-on in my own home, and has allowed me to perform actions to assure my overall physical security."}
{"Author": "Anita", "Date": "on December 27, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love love love this", "Text": "Love love love this. I can even lock my front door without getting up off my fanny. Or rather... my husband can as he's the one who tells it to lock the front door... but... it links everything we want it to, and it is turning our home into a smart home"}
{"Author": "Robert W.", "Date": "on December 27, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Three Stars", "Text": "Does what it is supposed to."}
{"Author": "STM", "Date": "on December 26, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Smartthings - should be called \u201cSometimes\u201d", "Text": "Have used both Smartthings and Wink. In my experience, while Smartthings may be more versatile - Wink is more reliable and less time consuming. I also do not want to have to be a programmer or spend hours Googling \u2018Smarthings\u2019 to figure out how to make it do something.\n\nExamples: reliability - Zigbee sensors continuously drop off regardless of how many I have. Ease of use - Wink allows me to set user codes on my Schlage locks without having to download third-party scripts.\n\nI am sure Smartthings works great for people who have the technical/programming background and time to fiddle - but it is not for me."}
{"Author": "Cryph", "Date": "on December 26, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Go ahead and get your AWS account now. Amazon needs more money.", "Text": "I waited quite a while before jumping into an IoT environment, and only did it at a \"discounted\" price.\nI believed after a small amount of research that ST seemed like a viable solution, and flexible enough.\n\nAfter about 2-3 weeks with the device, and some on/off network devices to pair with it-- I honestly think it is by far the best value for such a system.\nAt this point, I've yet to suffer any serious outages.\n\nThere is some awesome flexibility to be offered when combining this with emulated hue bridges and such."}
{"Author": "oscar gonzalez", "Date": "on December 25, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Great.."}
