{"Author": "Doug Kreighbaum", "Date": "on December 23, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great system. Compatibility with about", "Text": "How did I live without this tech before. Great system. Compatibility with about eveything"}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on December 23, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Very flexible on devices not like other similar product like Nest who monopolize for their ...", "Text": "User friendly and sends email notification whenever updating software. Very flexible on devices not like other similar product like Nest who monopolize for their market. My house is now automated with combinations of different products suited for their purpose."}
{"Author": "Jerry", "Date": "on December 23, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Excellent home automation system!", "Text": "The hub was easy to setup and configure new items. Automation took some time to get used to, but like most things, once you get the hang of it it\u2019s very intuitive. We would like to use our Amazon Echo to control more functions (e.g., garage door opener, sensors, etc.,), but perhaps that will come in time.\n\nOnly down side is that the color LED control panel doesn\u2019t work well on my iPad, but does function correctly on my cell."}
