{"Author": "CMaloch", "Date": "on October 16, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "LOVE this hub. I was previously using Vera.", "Text": "I love this hub. I've been using it for a month or so now, and have no issues to speak of, beyond the initial pairing procedure being a little bit painful (I find that the best practice is to reset every device you want to add, as you are trying to add it, even if it's never been setup before on this or any other hub. Otherwise it never sees it.) The smartthings app on android is also very handy. It has widgets you can add to your home screen to perform various routines, and you can also setup your phone as a presence sensor and create routines based on it's presence. In my case, I use it to unlock my front door and turn on the living room light as soon as my phone is detected by the hub. The only flaw with this routine, is it runs the routine if I reboot my phone while within range of the hub, so I have to remember to lock it back again when I reboot. But I also have a fail safe routine setup to automatically lock the doors at specific times anyway, so even if I forget, it will get automatically locked soon anyhow."}
{"Author": "Brian s", "Date": "on October 16, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works as advertised, fast response", "Text": "I haven\u2019t tried other smart home hubs however can tell you that smart things works as advertised without any issues. Response speed is surprisingly fast and pits with other devices quickly."}
