{"Author": "Thomas Jirouschek", "Date": "on September 29, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Another quality product from Samsung.", "Text": "This does what it says. I linked this to a GE Smart Socket and can now control it with my phone."}
{"Author": "Kyle", "Date": "on September 29, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Smart things is a great smart hub", "Text": "Smart things hub was very easy to set up and recognizes most of my smart accessories quickly."}
{"Author": "Addicted To Amazon", "Date": "on September 29, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Simple, easy to use.", "Text": "Okay so I am not a fan of Cloud Z-wave Control but I have to say I kind of like this. I have a Fibaro controller as well, and while I use that as my main, I also used a Vera, but it has had issues. I decided to try this thing out, it is the only device I was able to get my GDZ garage door opener ot work with. The door opener still has issues but that is not an function of the Smartthings its because that device was poorly built.\n\nDiscovery: It discovered all my Hue Bridge devices almost immediatly after I plugged the unit in (I had to do a little more than that but it was that simple).\n\nApp: The app is decent, I would like a nice browser interface but I can live with the app. It works as needed and is simple for most users.\n\nAutomation: It needs a little work in the Scene/automation section while I can create Automation schedules I would like a bit more control over complicated scheduling, but that is why I have the other controller.\n\nThe one thing I really like is that even though it wont discover some older Z-wave devices I have (neither did my Fibaro), my Vera can see them, and I can group the Devices from the Vera and the Fibaro together and control them from the Hub. So if you are that deep into automation or you are just crazy like me it will bridge the gap."}
{"Author": "Vincent", "Date": "on September 28, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Would not recommend.", "Text": "Everything was working for a month, and now a mix and match of devices or a hit and miss. Even Samsung's own TV is glitchy. Would not recommend."}
