{"Author": "JAMIE", "Date": "on September 27, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Best smart hub out there!!", "Text": "Love it!!"}
{"Author": "Abhi", "Date": "on September 27, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Poor app and website. Kloodgy product.", "Text": "Extremely difficult to use app and website. To start, the aignup process on website will give you option to signup using samsung or smarthimgs account. Why do I care?\nAdding family to your account is non-intuitive. Once added their accounts and setting up app, their phones are not shown on app, even after a day. After jumping through hoops to make geo fencing work, it still does not show them.\nSpend an astonishing 4 hours on this\n\nMy reccomendation: save yourmoney and wait for a better product."}
{"Author": "E. Lafnitzegger", "Date": "on September 26, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "My smart deadbolt can't stay connected and the hub is 20 ...", "Text": "Would have expected a longer range. My smart deadbolt can't stay connected and the hub is 20 feet away. Easy set up and Alexa connected with no problem."}
{"Author": "K. McIntyre", "Date": "on September 26, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great", "Text": "Love it. Looking forward to more automation. Using INOVELLI PLUGS and they work well together."}
{"Author": "Mattmoon9", "Date": "on September 25, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great Z-Wave Hub", "Text": "I have several Z-wave switches that I previously used as fancy timers with my alarm panel. Now that I have this set up as the controller, I love the options, app interface and expansion options I have for the future."}
{"Author": "Super-Elastic", "Date": "on September 25, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "The one thing you need to know for a non-frustrating experience", "Text": "Never, ever check the box for \"device health\" on the settings menu (though you can uncheck it if you do). Device health is supposed to improve the reliability of connected devices, but in reality it does just the opposite. I was banging my head in frustration thinking that I had not developed a sufficiently dense Z-wave mesh and kept futilely adding unneeded outlet switches to improve range so that my Kwikset locks and other devices would not disconnect after a day or two. Instead, all I had to do was uncheck the device health setting in order to keep everything connected and working properly."}
{"Author": "F. Lemaitre", "Date": "on September 24, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Much better than Vera", "Text": "Much better than Vera"}
{"Author": "Ray", "Date": "on September 22, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Range is a bit poor", "Text": "Works great as long as things are in range. 30 to 40ft through one wall is about all I get."}
{"Author": "rob", "Date": "on September 22, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Save your money!", "Text": "Unreliable! Contact support and they tell you the hub is too far. Balogne! They don't have the technology yet. Great ideaand it is great, when it works. Which is only sometimes. Very annoying when you open the app and expect something to turn off and it doesn't. I would not recommend smart things...Not yet."}
{"Author": "Ronnie Hayes", "Date": "on September 21, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Easy intuitive set up"}
{"Author": "Rick", "Date": "on September 21, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Good Alexa integration - works with other non Samsung smart components", "Text": "Good Alexa integration - works well via app interface. Syncing new wireless switches / modules quite simple, and it's just as easy to rename each one via the app. Thus, whatever you name it, that's what you tell your Amazon Echo to operate (i.e. Alexa, turn on the kitchen lights, etc)"}
{"Author": "Courtney Calvert", "Date": "on September 20, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works great for us and our needs.", "Text": "Super simple set up, had zero issue thus far. App is really easy to understand and manage."}
{"Author": "Chuck Turner", "Date": "on September 20, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easy Install. Great Product.", "Text": "So easy to install (aka plug it into the router and a power outlet). I currently only have it paired with a door lock. It was easy to pair and the app is intuitive and works well with my lock (Yale Electronic Deadbolt Zwave)."}
{"Author": "Alex", "Date": "on September 19, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Find something more reliable", "Text": "I'm not sure this is worth the effort. It constantly disconnects and I have to re-do settings for my cameras to record (I'm using arlo cams)."}
{"Author": "Phil", "Date": "on September 18, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Recommended but loses connection briefly every once in a while", "Text": "Works really well but seems to reboot more often than needed. Always back online and connected in just a minute or so though..."}
{"Author": "P.L", "Date": "on September 18, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Excellent device to control all kinds of devices", "Text": "Excellent device to control all kinds of devices. Only thing I don't like is the app is very limited compared to the manufacturer's apps to control devices with multiple functions like thermostats. For the rest is good. I use it with light bulbs, outlets, water leak sensors, smoke and carbon monoxide detector, and thermostats."}
{"Author": "Sheryl D.", "Date": "on September 17, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Love this hub.It's excellent.."}
{"Author": "Sree", "Date": "on September 16, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Nice product for reasonable price.\nit works as described."}
{"Author": "SteVac", "Date": "on September 15, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Not reliable enough", "Text": "I have Z-wave plus switches and receptacles throughout my home and nothing I can do will provide a reliable mesh network. I have some devices literally 10 feet away from others and some come and go in and out of operation. My old X10 system using 1975 technology was far more reliable. My return date was 10 days ago so this was an expensive experiment."}
{"Author": "Ryan Stasel", "Date": "on September 15, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Wish I\u2019d purchased ages ago!!!", "Text": "As a wink user, I kept hearing how great ST was. Completely open, community driven, etc. I purchased on one of the $49.99 sales, and boy howdy, was everyone right (and more). I\u2019ve never seen so many possibilities. Between webcore, and the rboy add-ons, I have my home automation doing stuff that I only dreamed of with Wink.\n\nSo, now my Wink Hub lives in the kitchen cabinet handling my cabinet lighting tied to a Lutron Connected Remote (Smartthings doesn\u2019t allow the cool \u201c4 Button mode\u201d of these remotes like Wink does).\n\nSeriously, if you want to up your home automation game, ST is the way to go!"}
{"Author": "Stan in Lake Havasu City", "Date": "on September 14, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Does what it is supposed to do. So far ...", "Text": "Does what it is supposed to do. So far I have tested it with the echo dot, the GE series of switches and dimmers, a Lutron dimmer (requires adding the Lutron hub) a fibaro flood sensor and some in the box modules. All seem to work as intended after you get past the setup and pairing issues. Will see how it works long term"}
{"Author": "Mark N.", "Date": "on September 14, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works well.", "Text": "Works as designed, no issues after several months."}
{"Author": "AudreyP", "Date": "on September 13, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Not ready for Prime Time", "Text": "Unfortunately you can't give an item zero stars, so I was stuck gifting this boat anchor a single star. Tried to use it to replace a hub in an existing, working system so that I could connect the zwave devices to my Echo. This hub failed to learn a single device. Tech support claims there is 'noise' on my AC lines (well yeah, they're AC lines), but could not explain why the old system works fine. Avoid this one and go with the wink."}
{"Author": "Redsnake", "Date": "on September 12, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Awesome hub.", "Text": "Awesome hub. Very easy to setup and connect. Excellent online chat support for tech questions. Easy to setup conditions, routines and notifications."}
{"Author": "DanoSLC", "Date": "on September 10, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easy and works", "Text": "Wow was this easy to set up. Love it"}
{"Author": "Jenna & Tim Smallidge", "Date": "on September 10, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Horrible", "Text": "Hard to tell if it's the hub or sensors, but the system is unreliable with constant false alarms. I've done several periodic checks over the past 9 months and I always find at least 1 sensor which isn't communicating with the hub any more. There's no fault or indications to me, I just stumble across these hidden failures. Other sensors are contanstly giving false alarm for no apparent reason. Also the app to control everything is difficult to setup and use and takes many steps to dismiss an alarm."}
{"Author": "DaveJ", "Date": "on September 10, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works with Hue Hub and Alexa.", "Text": "I've added several z-wave devices and a Hue hub and all have been working fine for months. My devices are also linked with Alexa allowing voice automation."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on September 10, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "must have", "Text": "great buy"}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on September 10, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "You need a wired internet connection", "Text": "The issue I have with this device is that is not wireless so you can't just place anywhere you like in your house, you will need a wired internet connection. Other than that it works just fine. The best way to use it is to get zwave boosters for areas that are far from it."}
{"Author": "Wolf Z", "Date": "on September 6, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "NICE"}
{"Author": "fitz spring", "Date": "on September 5, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "it was great and work well, but I could not use it"}
{"Author": "The Miami IT Guy", "Date": "on September 4, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "It's the best of both worlds. Smartthings is a commercially supported product with an extremely active community.", "Text": "For me its the perfect package for those who dont want to go full pro like crestron or HomeAssistant\\OpenHAB. Install webcore and you have all the scripting you need. It's the best of both worlds. Smartthings is a commercially supported product with an extremely active community."}
{"Author": "amix", "Date": "on September 3, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "... hub 2 because samsung smartthings did not detected my smart lock even after keeping them in kissing distance", "Text": "I got wink hub 2 because samsung smartthings did not detected my smart lock even after keeping them in kissing distance."}
{"Author": "Jeff Staffon", "Date": "on September 2, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Samsung has done an excellent job!", "Text": "I've spent the last several years playing with open-source z-wave software and devices using a Raspberry Pi as the controller. I wanted something more reliable ...\"in production\" ... that would use all my devices and be compatible with the z-wave protocol. All of my devices paired with the Smarthings Hub and works flawlessly. Samsung has done an excellent job!"}
{"Author": "Roberto Hudson", "Date": "on September 2, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Works great."}
{"Author": "jonathan kemper", "Date": "on September 1, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Samsung is still working out some bugs, but this is a must have for home automation."}
{"Author": "Captain Insano", "Date": "on August 31, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Not very smart. Look elsewhere for \"smart\"", "Text": "Shaky system. Loses connection, poor interface. Not really that smart. I've had to reset the stupid thing 3 times, that includes having to reconnect all my devices."}
{"Author": "Victor Gomez", "Date": "on August 31, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "This hub is pretty good, and price is better", "Text": "This hub is pretty good, and price is better. If you like monitoring your home this is the right purchase."}
{"Author": "Richard K. Lee", "Date": "on August 31, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Works well..."}
{"Author": "Psi", "Date": "on August 31, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Does what it says.", "Text": "Does what it says."}
{"Author": "Sharon James", "Date": "on August 30, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "The best hub", "Text": "This hub works perfect in my smart home. All my devices work with Alexa through this hub. this is very easy to set up with the app on my phone."}
{"Author": "James R. Garner", "Date": "on August 30, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works... some connectivity issues at times.", "Text": "Works...some connectivity issues at times."}
{"Author": "V. DANG", "Date": "on August 30, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "easy: Otherwise", "Text": "Under fifteen min to go through the very straightforward set up. I did have to purchase a port switch since I didn't have room but another ten bucks gave me options to connect even more things! Here's the one I got.. easy: TP-Link 5-Port Fast Ethernet Desktop Switch (TL-SF1005D) Otherwise, it comes w everything you need in the box.\n\nNote that some devices will require you to have the hub physically near it to pair so do that before installing. I had a bit of issue w the Schlage lock becuase I had already installed it on the front door and was really too lazy to disconnect or uninstall either of them to bring them closer together so I carefully nudged them both to closer proximity (i believe 10 ft is the suggested min) and lucked out that they found each other. Together forever now!"}
{"Author": "Jon Capps", "Date": "on August 29, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Four Stars", "Text": "works well"}
{"Author": "Michael F. Campbell", "Date": "on August 28, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "What is the point if automation requires programmer skills?", "Text": "Requires a doctorate in computer programming. Otherwise, great equipment. If only the average consumer could use it. It does make a great paperweight."}
{"Author": "IamByrdMan", "Date": "on August 28, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Awesome even Awesomer", "Text": "When you need help with code to make devices work fully the way they should see rboyapps dot c@m\nSome devices you buy and install are seen as the wrong device type or the closes device type doesn't use all the sensors. Roy Boy writes all sorts of scrips for all sorts of devices. We chat regularly about ongoing projects. Requests are filled on a regular. His stuff is so good I bought a lifetime membership even if I'll have everything I need in a week or 2.\n\nrboyapps has saved 3 devices for me so far. I would have trashed them without their help. Saved me 4 times the cost of membership! Great deal and awesome personal service."}
{"Author": "Dave R", "Date": "on August 27, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Four Stars", "Text": "Seems to work great even with my Hue products"}
{"Author": "maurice a. grant jr", "Date": "on August 27, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Two Stars", "Text": "My hub was suspose to be new it had no instructions very disappointing."}
{"Author": "HJW", "Date": "on August 27, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "ok", "Text": "ok"}
{"Author": "Gatorfan66", "Date": "on August 27, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "The only smart home hub you need.", "Text": "This is the best option for home automation everything else is an over priced copy without Samsung support. This hub will connect to any wifi enabled smart home device. Door locks, lighting, thermostat and with a echo dot it takes voice commands."}
{"Author": "Chris D.", "Date": "on August 26, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Loving this hub so far!", "Text": "Loving this hub so far! The setup was really simple and I was up and running in maybe 10 minutes if that.\nRight now I just have a small setup with a couple smart bulbs and switches but I will be expanding my setup to see what else this can do.\nThe only downside I can think of would be that this is a cloud based unit. Meaning most commands run though their servers rather than through the hub itself. It does some lighting functions locally but for everything else its cloud based. This is a con for most consumer hubs though.\nThat being said everything has been smooth. I have yet to experience any lag time between commands or any misfires."}
{"Author": "David Martinez", "Date": "on August 26, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Extremely easy to setup, the ability to use Alexa to activate is also extremely convenient"}
{"Author": "A. Karjoo", "Date": "on August 26, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Good unit, but loses connectivity - updated review", "Text": "I decided to get this to replace a staples connect unit. I like the functionality it has to exclude a previous device pairing. It seems to work faster. It has more options to program events. Issues I have are initially my Zwave door lock. It lost connectivity and device was not available. Then it came back after a few days. A few days ago the whole unit lost coonectibuty the came back faster a few hours but My iris garage door opener is now showing not available. It's been a week and has not returned. I may exclude it and reassociate to try and fix. So I think it's good, nice functionality. Works fast, easy to work with, just took one star off because of the connectivity issues I mentioned earlier. Also price had decreased by 50%... oh well.\n\nUpdate\nSo I have no more connectivity issues. Modules that I had issues with, I removed from the list/ forced exclusion and reassociated and now everything works well. The response on the modules from the App is very good and fast. You can program alerts like your garage door is open or turn off all lights and adjust thermostat when you leave the house and turn back on when to return, etc. I am not sure what the initial connectivity issues were but all have gone. I like this very much, the price fluctuates between 50-100,"}
{"Author": "Roy Reese", "Date": "on August 26, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I have not been able to get the app working ...", "Text": "I have not been able to get the app working on my Android device. No link to my door locks!"}
{"Author": "V. Biggs", "Date": "on August 26, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works very well and easy to setup smart devices", "Text": "Works very well and easy to setup smart devices. There can be a very slight delay when Alexa is giving it the command but it is not significant. I have it controlling my schlage lock and it works great allowing me to unlock the door when I am not home if necessary. I like the fact that Alexa will take a voice command to lock the door but will not unlock the door. Seems more secure. If you are using it with Alexa you first need to set up the devices with SmartThings and then import the devices into Alexa."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on August 26, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "100%"}
{"Author": "Ricky Preslar", "Date": "on August 25, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Great, Thank you"}
{"Author": "KEVIN K", "Date": "on August 24, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Intermittently works well.", "Text": "The idea of this tool is great. I bought this with a z-wave fan switch. It is connected to amazon Alexa and works about 70% of the time to do what is asked. Other times Alexa says \"ok\" as if smart things responded appropriately but the action is not completed."}
{"Author": "xue rui", "Date": "on August 23, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "It works great with the Schlage lock and Rboy smart application", "Text": "It works great with the Schlage lock and Rboy smart application. And they have great technical support. I got what I want. Bye-bye Wink hub!"}
{"Author": "CHUCK K.", "Date": "on August 23, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easy to navigate with a user friendly app", "Text": "No problems with this hub. Everything connects, mainly Zwave wall switches at this point. Easy to navigate with a user friendly app."}
{"Author": "M.Campos", "Date": "on August 23, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Very Good but Lutron switches need extra!", "Text": "I like the overall product size, build capability but if you have Lutron Caseta switches you will still require a Lutron bridge (about $80). I was trying to replace my Wink but the Wink has Lutron's clear connect language natively. The smartthings sadly does not. I would prefer to keep my setup as simple as possible"}
{"Author": "Lizzy P", "Date": "on August 22, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Just what I needed", "Text": "Works perfect with my smart lock. Easy to download and use. Did not have to make any calls for help."}
{"Author": "Bob P Wilson", "Date": "on August 22, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great.", "Text": "Great"}
{"Author": "twin11", "Date": "on August 21, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Stable and easy to use", "Text": "The system works flawlessly and is amazing. They really tweeked it and it is super stable/easy to operate now."}
{"Author": "WTF", "Date": "on August 21, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Best home automation platform out there. Highly recommend.", "Text": "Best home automation platform out there. Highly recommend."}
{"Author": "Donna G.", "Date": "on August 20, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Can't add TP-Link devices"}
{"Author": "Paul H. Brassard", "Date": "on August 20, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Samsung Support HELPED ME!!", "Text": "Samsung's Support really helped me out when I got locked out of it because I lost the login and password. Contacted them on their 'CHAT' site and they couldn't be more helpful. The Tech even offered to remotely CLEAR it so I could start over and re-set it up. I chose to follow his instructions on how to do it myself, and was successful on my first try. I now have the Password & Login in a safe place! I then was easily able to tell ALEXA to work with the HUB. Now 'SHE\" is in control. Guess it's time to buy more goodies for her to control."}
{"Author": "Amazon Fan", "Date": "on August 20, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Died after 2 days of use", "Text": "I've been using Wink, and it was time to upgrade. I purchased the SmartThings hub, started to set it up, and the thing just died. Now it has been 30 days since I bought it so I can't return it. Back to Wink for me. Stay away from Samsung unless you want your stuff to die unexpectedly and/or catch fire."}
{"Author": "Hasan Mahmood", "Date": "on August 19, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Good hub!", "Text": "Great stuff, works as expected."}
{"Author": "Ray Bishop", "Date": "on August 19, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Constantly shows connected devices as unavailable. --- Update: 08/22/2017 - issue resolved with zwave repeaters.", "Text": "I regret buying this product. As other users has posted. The product constantly goes off line and shows as unavailable. I purchased this product and enrolled 2 locks - one dead bolt and one lever lock. I've had the product for a week and even now, it's showing both locks on the smart things apps as unavailable. It constantly drops off and, as written on other's postings, it mysteriously shows available later.\n\nMy IP camera I paid $100 bucks for stays connected and that's OFF BRAND!!\n\nProblem is, it may not be working at the time you needed it. I just purchased some z-wave repeaters to strengthen the signal, but my experience has really shaken my confidence in the product as I was hoping I can use to allow entry into my home by guest when I'm not there. If extenders doesn't work, WINK, you will have a new customer...don't disappoint me as Samsung has with this product!\n\nUpdate: 08/22/2017. I have received my repeaters and they've been installed for 24 hours now and it appears to have fixed my connectivity issues. So my issue seems to have been interference and signal strength. I have not had any drop offs or unavailable status since I've installed the z-wave repeaters. I did not change the post as it could help others who, like me, goes to the comments containing the complaints. So with the repeaters, I would give the product 5 STARs. Sticking with Smart Things. Hope it continues working.\n\nRB\nClinton, MD"}
{"Author": "F. Brammer", "Date": "on August 18, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I like Smartthings technology, but I don't think it's ready for everyone.", "Text": "Smartthings... Hmmm... Okay, when everything works and goes straight forward it seems pretty simple and smart. If thing don't go well and you have to swap out hubs or reconfigure things, well you are in for a real treat. I really didn't think I was an early adopter of this technology.\n\n1. If you swapping out hubs, make sure you unpair all your devices and make sure they unpaired successfully.\n2. Don't return or get rid of the old hub until you are sure all devices are paired to the new hub.\n(There are tools to fix this if you mess up, but that's another step.)\n3. You may have issues getting the second hub with the smartthings cloud.\n4. You may have issues getting the second hub working with Alexa.\n\nI was okay with the troubleshooting and work, but would think most people would find it very frustrating."}
{"Author": "Asha", "Date": "on August 16, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Work in progress.", "Text": "It has a learning curve. Still trying to set up everything without duplicating routines and rules. My 1 gripe is the limitation with Schlage Locks, could only unlock full potential buy using a custom setting."}
{"Author": "Alexandre", "Date": "on August 16, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Amazing product! Get all your home connected!", "Text": "I've bought the SmartThings because I wanted to integrate my home with Alexa and take benefit the possible automation.\nIt works really good and the step by step is easy to follow. Once is connected on the internet , you just have to click on \"find a thing\" and it will detected the smart devices that you have.\nI have some sengled smart bulbs, some GE switches and some smart plugs as well. All of them paired very easily without trouble.\nAfter having all the devices recognized by the SmartThings hub, all you need to do is to go to alexa, enable the SmartThings skill and click on \"discover\" so it will find out the devices.\nI have created several groups, so I'm able now to turn on, turn off and control my devices on different rooms. I can ask Alexa to turn on the lights on my kitchen, or on my kitchen table, or even on the whole kitchen all together. Very easy to handle with different groups.\nWorks really well! Now I can relax and do most of the stuff through voice control!"}
{"Author": "k.", "Date": "on August 16, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "don't use with Z wave devices.", "Text": "does not well with z wave products. Worked fine initially, but with app updates and difficulty with communication with Alexa I gave up. It may work with other automation devices but avoid this hub with z wave devices."}
{"Author": "Anthony Eggleston", "Date": "on August 15, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Price drop 10 days later, what the crap.", "Text": "When I bought this hub it was 98 dollars, that was on August 4th 2017, now the price dropped to 49, 10 days later... What the crap... It's a great product but I feel like I was slightly ripped off."}
{"Author": "Steven", "Date": "on August 15, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easy to install and set up", "Text": "Easy to install and set up. It now controls several key devices in my house enabling me to control things on the go."}
{"Author": "Sam S", "Date": "on August 15, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "NO Web-Based Monitoring Option Provided", "Text": "We travel internationally part of the year. After returning home several trips ago to find water on the floor from a broken refrigerator ice maker line, I decided to install some leak detectors so I could monitor any water leaks. Two weeks of having a professional service dry my hardwood floors was enough motivation. I had already set-up Arlo home security cameras and Nest smoke detectors for web-based monitoring. So doing the same with leak detectors made sense.\n\nAfter researching leak detectors, I decided on the ones offered by SmartThings. I liked the small size and the fact there were no wires or electric plugs involved. I installed them and was very happy with how they worked, though it did take some tinkering.\n\nThen I discovered a serious limitation. Samsung SmartThings does NOT provide a web-monitoring portal, like I'm used to with Arlo or Nest. Instead, I am forced to monitor only through my Android phone. This isn't a problem except when I am traveling internationally where I use a local throwaway phone. Of course, that's why I got the detectors to start with, because of my travel. Not being able to monitor by web internationally is a problem.. If I had known, I would have kept looking.\n\nI confirmed this \"no web-based monitoring\" limitation with Samsung SmartThings customer support. That's correct-no web-based monitoring, they said, but web-based monitoring is not common for home device monitoring (I'm always uplifted to have a company tell me that my needs are not legitimate in order to justify a problematic product design). But I have Arlo and Nest, I said, both of which provide web-based monitoring. True, they said, but they are not complete smart home solutions. (So what? I'm thinking) According to the rep, there are no plans by Samsung SmartThings to provide web-based monitoring.\n\nUnfortunately, I didn't research well enough to uncover this limitation. I'm posting this review just in case it helps someone else avoid a similar mistake."}
{"Author": "Anthony C", "Date": "on August 15, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Alexa, SmartThings, and Lights, DO NOT CONNECT!!!", "Text": "I bought the recommended items, Amazon Alexa and Samsung SmartThings and so far, NOTHING WORKS. They are each individually set up, but will not connect to one-another. I finally decided to use the USB cord to connect Alexa to the SmartThings hub, so that connection is made. The SmartThings hub recognizes the lights, but in the app, changing the name and saving the changes is absolutely IMPOSSIBLE. I know the connection with the lights have been made, because they blinked 3 times and now when I turn them on, it is just a white light. Before the connection, it would cycle through the RGB colors. I have updated my iPhone and each of the apps, I am pretty tech savy, but this has me absolutely frustrated."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on August 14, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Got a refurbished/used one", "Text": "Was very excited to get this on a deal for $49.99. However, it feels like they provided me with a used/refurbished piece since the packaging seemed to be opened already.\nAlso, when I first set it up, it didn't work at all, and had to reset it again and try to get it work.\nVery disappointed!"}
{"Author": "N. Keeling", "Date": "on August 14, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Four Stars", "Text": "Zigbee support lacking some but overall works pretty well"}
