{"Author": "Extra Copy", "Date": "on August 9, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Does not work very well with Schlage Locks on Zwave", "Text": "Sorry but this just did not do what I wanted which was offer fully supported functionality of schlage locks. It did a very poor job supporting that at best. It should be noted in the reviews that it really does not work yet with schlage. It connected quite easily and did all that was promised in setup but then only locked/unlocked remotely, The interface was poor and stark at best, had no awareness of if it was locked or unlocked status and did not support any remote code management of the lock. Maybe it works better with other things but unfortunately I was forced to test out and return."}
{"Author": "Adam Davenport Bradley \ud83c\udfb6", "Date": "on August 9, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Starter product, with some amateurish shortcomings", "Text": "Under normal conditions, it works well enough; while the app isn't exactly intuitive, once you know the magic incantations it's easy enough to get many straightforward use cases working.\n\nPretty much everything runs in the cloud -- which means nothing works if your internet connection is down. So avoid this product if your internet provider isn't top-tier for reliability.\n\nSamsung does regular system upgrades, which is good, but they're not done well; they require the hub going offline, not just for seconds but for half an hour, and are usually done during US hours when my system is in use by people awake and living in the house, instead of overnight when it is not.\n\nEven with the app exempted from battery optimization, it still doesn't reliably detect me coming within 2 miles of the house to run my \"returning home\" program.\n\nSo, it was good as a starter unit, but I'm now looking for alternatives."}
{"Author": "Lavalchiefs", "Date": "on August 9, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works great. I did download custom code (device handler) from ...", "Text": "Works great. I did download custom code (device handler) from Kevin LaFramboise - to support more granular features from my various devices - awesome, and thank you."}
