{"Author": "JLM", "Date": "on August 7, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Not as smart as hoped/expected", "Text": "Nice product in concept, but in practice/reality it didn't truly \"bring together\" too many of my devices well. For example, Arlo by Netgear cameras were easy to add, but it's not possible to adjust the recording time when controlled by SmartThings. Therefore, my cameras would only record for 10 seconds; as opposed to being able to decide between any amount from 10 seconds to 2 mins as you're able to do within the Arlo app without SmartThings. Recording for 10 seconds isn't useful and therefore I'm no longer using SmartThings as I'd hoped. Maybe it works well for other things but this was one of the \"out of the box\" products that it claims to work with and not doing so was a deal breaker for my needs. Also as an FYI, it still requires you to keep all the hubs and product specific accounts to use the SmartThings hub, so it doesn't replace all of that, rather it just \"controls\" the devices with which it's compatible. I didn't know this and while not a terrible thing, wanted to mention for others to know in advance. Hope this helps."}
