{"Author": "J Cormie", "Date": "on May 1, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Didn't work for me", "Text": "I'm sending SmartThings back. It wouldn't sync with my Schlage door lock. It's not compatible even though it states it is in the description section. You really have to make sure about compatibility. I"}
{"Author": "Zack", "Date": "on May 1, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "There is limited functionality within the SmartThings app and the navigation controls within the app are sub-par at best. It's h", "Text": "Unfortunately, this just makes things more hectic and confusing, while diminishing the capabilities of each individual app/product. There is limited functionality within the SmartThings app and the navigation controls within the app are sub-par at best. It's honestly easier to just use each singular app for the respective products, rather than using this. This hub just takes up space on my desk and uses more bandwidth and energy than it's worth."}
{"Author": "Vinnie505", "Date": "on April 30, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great wifi brain", "Text": "Awesome unit , highly recommend"}
{"Author": "jbr23", "Date": "on April 30, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Cool technology for good price", "Text": "So far so good, installed back in the middle of January. Still showing 100% battery after 4 months on all 3 sensors, not sure about the other people who complained about battery life, perhaps recent updates to the hub helped. They haven't got wet yet, so not sure about possible corrison of sensors. It does say to put 15' or so to hub, which is kind of inconvenient, but mine are a lot further than this and work fine. Overall, thus far I like the smart things setup and app. I also like that the app notifies me when the hub is offline like when my intenet or power goes out. Seems to work good and very reasonable price for not having to worry about water in our finished basement."}
{"Author": "Systems Host Inc.", "Date": "on April 30, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Best smarthub I have ever tried. Works very well."}
{"Author": "Tim Slater", "Date": "on April 28, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Super."}
{"Author": "mark spencer", "Date": "on April 27, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Smartthings NOT so smart", "Text": "Have had nothing but issues with this system. Support is great, but items do not live up to the Samsung name - my opinion. Has a very short working range and had to buy other modules to achieve a boosted signal to my front door (only 20' from hub). Ridiculously unfriendly and not well programmed for setting up a whole system. Needs a better icon/picture type of logic programming system that everyone can easily follow and achieve the results they want for their security needs. Camera does not notify me on entry opening nor does it capture clips. The door/window sensors are not being discovered by the hub at all. Beware of incompatibility issues between Z-wave and Zigbee devices - why people seriously? For the money I have already spent I am not at all impressed with the software or hardware performance."}
{"Author": "David W", "Date": "on April 27, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Really happy with it.", "Text": "Works great. It's been very reliable and I'm slowly expanding it to control more and more. Not sure I could ever go back to a dumb house :)"}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on April 26, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works as advertised", "Text": "Great hub, no issues with it so far."}
{"Author": "KYSlate91", "Date": "on April 26, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "This made all the smart home stuff I bought work", "Text": "This made all the smart home stuff I bought work. If you don't own this your in the Stone Age."}
{"Author": "Bruce Kinley, MN, RN", "Date": "on April 26, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Best hub system on the market.", "Text": "Samsung SmartThings wins the smart home battle! There are so many different items by various manufacturers that work with SmartThings. You still need to be careful because some items will only work with Wink or another hub. But so far, I am very impressed with this hub. I use it for my clients for smart home monitoring. The app for smart phones also works well (I do wish they had one for iPad). And the website and support are so helpful. It is open source so there is a large community of developers and others with creative solutions. If you are new to smart home automation - start here with SmartThings. Buy your hub first!!! Then buy different components that are compatible."}
{"Author": "MeinkePhotos", "Date": "on April 26, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great Automation", "Text": "Lots of features and compatibility. I can even trigger a connected light switch to the motion sensor on my Ring doorbell."}
{"Author": "JBDekes", "Date": "on April 25, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Recommend a different hub, unstable and poor up-time reliability-- STAY AWAY", "Text": "Well, to say the least, this thing does NOT work most of the time. Good thing I purchased this to test the functionality and not actually install in my home.\n\nVERY dissatisfied with the connectivity issues, lack of ability to disable updates (sometimes updates are good, MOST are bad for functionality when installed in a home).\n\nHave tested a competitive brand (starts with V and Ends Rith A) and it is MUCH more stable, reliable, etc.\n\nWill NOT be using this product for my home, or my customers as I need my home lighting, alarming, and video cams to work ALL THE TIME. Minimum amount of downtime is CRITICAL in home automation and this product does not offer that level of dependency."}
{"Author": "Milton Cross", "Date": "on April 24, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Purchased Dec 16, died Apr. 23, Customer ...", "Text": "Purchased Dec 16, died Apr. 23, Customer support will not replace unit, but will have me do an hour software update and go through a procedure for removing each device and repairing devices and set everything up from scratch. 4 hour project and this is the 2nd time this happened in 4 months. Not reliable and Samsung is not helpful. They said this is just a home monitoring system and should not be relied upon for secure measures, customer support person verbatim. Go with Homeseer."}
{"Author": "C. Garber", "Date": "on April 24, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Power users, prepare to be very frustrated!", "Text": "This is the most frustrating piece of hardware I have ever put in my home. There is no \"figuring this out\". It's buggy and has many known issues. I've had this hub since it was released.\n\nIf you have 5-10 devices, you're fine. You probably won't see most of the issues I've been dealing with. It's when you replace all your home light switches, garage doors, and dead bolts that you see the many issues.\n\nI have 153 devices on my z-wave network. WELL under the 240 that this system is advertised to support. None the less, SmartThings support continues to blame \"Z-wave network traffic\" as the culprit.\n\nThe issues include:\n- Devises no longer responding to commands from the app.\n- Light switches just reverse direction (down makes the light turn on, up makes the light turn off)\n- Blue LED notifications just flip (Set to glow when the light is on, but glows when the light is off)\n- Randomly, triggers such as outside lights will work and will not work\n- System will just NOT respond to a light on/off command or be delayed 30+ seconds.\n\nThese issues aren't few and far between. They are a daily occurrence. When a random switch stops working with the app you have to remove it from the hub and add it back in. This sounds easy but it's flaky and frustrating like the rest of this system. Sometimes you can remove it, sometimes you have to spend 10 minutes unregistering it 5+ times. To makes matters worse, it randomly will unregister other switches instead, exacerbating the problem.\n\nThen you need to add it. This is another frustrating 10+ minute project. It will add the switch incorrectly (which means you need to remove it and add it again), it'll actually have not unregistered it (despite telling you it did) so you have to go back in and unregister it again, or it'll just not find it.\n\nI love the possibilities of this system and what it can do. These problems completely kill the experience. There is no fix for these problems. I had them in hub 1 and continue to have them in hub 2. Support is worthless as they give you the same canned response. \"Pull the power toggle on the switch\", \"Power cycle the hub\", \"Remove the device and readd it\". If you only want 10 or so smart devices, get this! If not prepare to be unbelievably irritated."}
{"Author": "Donnie J. Dennison", "Date": "on April 22, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great Purchase", "Text": "Figuring this out more and more as I go along. Love it!"}
{"Author": "sam6959", "Date": "on April 22, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Only lock and unlocks! No code generating capibilities.", "Text": "I was under the impression that this hub will allow me to generate codes. According to Schlage, I can't. Just lock and unlock. That sucks! It might be useful to others, but useless for me rental cabin. Returning the product. I was told to go with Wink or Iris to be able to have such abilities."}
{"Author": "john", "Date": "on April 22, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "I love this unit (so far). It was easy to install, easy to download the app, and works accurately."}
{"Author": "Rusty B Mckay", "Date": "on April 21, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "great"}
{"Author": "procmc", "Date": "on April 18, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Perfect"}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on April 18, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I did research into all the new smart hubs. My main use as of right now ...", "Text": "This is my first time ever leaving a review, but I feel that it is needed. I did research into all the new smart hubs. My main use as of right now was to increase the security in my home, turning my home into a smart one was just a bonus. I was skeptical reading some of the reviews about smarthings. I've had my system for 3 weeks now and haven't had 1 single issue. I've found smarthings to reliable and easy to use. I haven't had any false alarms, or any issue connecting any devices! Absolutely love it!"}
{"Author": "Monte See", "Date": "on April 17, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Installed easy. Down loaded ap. No problems"}
{"Author": "FirstDown17", "Date": "on April 17, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Well, at least it didn't blow up!", "Text": "Complete Junk. The code doesn't work (right out of the box)...And you basically need an act of Congress to reset it, including picture taking of the box, SKU, sent to multiple emails addresses. Nope!"}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on April 17, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "so easy to set up! it's great!"}
{"Author": "Jspyhotmail", "Date": "on April 16, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Nice all round choice for many apps", "Text": "I liked this hub, I it all depends on your application and background but I found it easy to setup for basic and fairly flexible and powerful enough for some higher end applications."}
{"Author": "Vijay Kumar", "Date": "on April 15, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Nice that it does so many different protocols. User interface could stand some improvement."}
{"Author": "bulldog222a", "Date": "on April 15, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Does not control time related smart apps", "Text": "All the time related smart apps do not work with start and end times, or with sunrise or sunset, making the hub worthless!!!"}
{"Author": "ml", "Date": "on April 14, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works as advertised", "Text": "Received as Xmas gift. Connected one summer switch, one leak sensor and all the lights on hue hub. Little hiccup with the summer switch but got it done. Only on day 3 but so far so good. Set up some notifications for the leak sensor and pushed them through tasker app. Looking forward to adding on more."}
{"Author": "Dominick Delio", "Date": "on April 14, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Simple to use, responsive and compatible with a wide range of products."}
{"Author": "coop", "Date": "on April 14, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "More money!!", "Text": "Excellent device but you might as well get ready to purchase several signal repeaters,89.00 for hub and 29.00 to 50.00 each for the signal repeaters to get my door locks to work"}
{"Author": "A. Kotula", "Date": "on April 13, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Smart home", "Text": "This is definitely the way to go for home automation! The smart home!"}
{"Author": "Michael P. Utke", "Date": "on April 11, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great product for home automation, works with Google Home.", "Text": "This works great for home automation. It can be used with the Samsung app, to control all sorts of devices around your home. So far I have only used it with light bulbs and light switches, but it works great. In the app you can see what is on and what is off. Additionally you can put devices on a timer. For instance, my front lights go on twenty minutes after sunset; so there are options beyond just setting a time. The Android app has a widget to quickly execute a command without opening the app.\nThis Hub can operate as a bridge between Google Home and the Z-Wave or other smart technology. It works great. The app also lists which devices are at \"Home\", if that's helpful."}
{"Author": "KMMR", "Date": "on April 11, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works great. App is easy. Love my smart home!", "Text": "I picked up the Samsung HUB to be the \"brain\" for my smart home system and I couldn't be happier with it. Keep in mind this review is being written by an IT professional.... The device was pretty easy to install and get up and running. The app is pretty easy to use. Adding \"things\" to the HUB was pretty simple as well... my main issue there had to do with the \"things\" I was installing, not the HUB. So far the device has functioned exactly how I thought it would and and I am very happy with it."}
{"Author": "AJ", "Date": "on April 10, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "but you also have the ability to code custom automation applications which is pretty awesome!", "Text": "If you're starting to get your feet wet with home automation, this is a must have for your environment. I have noticed that any devices that have the ability to natively integrate with the Smartthings Hub have a shorter lead time and are more responsive to set off triggers when compared to IFTTT. I use Smartthings to manage everything from my door sensors, Philips Hue lights, WeMo light switches, and Z Wave sirens. I haven't had a chance to play with it yet, but you also have the ability to code custom automation applications which is pretty awesome!"}
{"Author": "newguyinhk", "Date": "on April 10, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "good product.", "Text": "Smooth functioning, good product."}
{"Author": "G. Wagner", "Date": "on April 10, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Very few complaints - does everything it is supposed to do", "Text": "This was my first smart hub. The only reason I only gave it 4 stars is because setting up smart routines is not as simple or intuitive as it could be. I also have trouble getting the hub to recognize when my wife and my phones arrive and leave. At least I don't think it does. When I look at the history I can often see them leaving but not arriving. How does it know it left if it doesn't show me that it arrived prior to that. It could just be a quirk in the app. I don't feel like I can depend on smart routines that depend on the phones leaving or arriving because of that.\n\nI also wish they had a desktop app for controlling the hub and devices. There are some things that would just be much easier configuring on a larg screen instead of on a phone screen.\n\nI have no complaints about reliability or up-time. I also have almost no trouble with coverage. I did have an issue setting up connected Cree bulbs outside of the house. I had to get the hub to recognize them inside the house because it couldn't detect them outside. Then I moved them outside and they are controlled with a smart routine or through Alexa with no problems. Weird that you can't set them up outside but there is no problem controlling them. I guess it is the brick walls causing the problem because they are no further from my hub than other devices in the house.\n\nI had some issues re-syncing the devices when I moved into a new house but eventually was able to work those issues out by removing the skill from Alexa and adding it back in. Until I did that, Alexa had all of my old device names showing as offline as well as all of my new device names. It was mostly annoying and I don't know if that could be considered any SmartThings problem or not.\n\nI have been able to connect every device that SmartThings said it would connect. I had trouble getting a connected switch to work again after I moved it but after I quit trying to remove it from ST and just renamed it instead, everything was good."}
{"Author": "Mark Scott", "Date": "on April 10, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "This has revolutionized our household. Our primary use for ...", "Text": "This has revolutionized our household. Our primary use for this was with a Yale Z-Wave Real Living Key Free Touchscreen Deadbolt. We have created schedules to allows our older children to come home without the use of a key. We were pleasantly surprised to find out it works with our WeMo devices as well (This is in Samsung Labs and not \"officially\" supported\")! Combined with Alexa we've been able to fulfill our home automation tasks with little effort. We've even integrated our IP camera. If you're on the fence about a hub, pick the one that integrates all of the protocols into one box."}
{"Author": "mike milburn", "Date": "on April 10, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I was originally told i needed this for my new ...", "Text": "I was originally told i needed this for my new samsung connected fridge but then was later told that it was not needed\nNow the return policy is expired and I'm stuck with it. annoying"}
{"Author": "Dana Gibson", "Date": "on April 9, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I really want to like this product and the various items that can be ...", "Text": "I bought this to experiment with simple home automation of lights (turn on when I get home, turn off when I leave, etc). I really want to like this product and the various items that can be programmed for the home. Unfortunately, I'm using at a vacation home - not my full-time home - and its been installed for about 90 days and has worked for maybe 10 days TOTAL. It goes \"offline\" randomly for weeks at a time, then mysteriously comes back \"online\" for a day or two, then back \"offline\" again. So, it's basically useless. I cannot run over to reboot manually and rebooting remotely through the SmartThings website has never worked. Not even once. For the short time it was working I really liked the customization of lights and being able to check a SmartCam that's set up. Thank goodness we are NOT using this for security (door/window contacts, motion detection). Much more work is required for this to be at all useful."}
{"Author": "Paul K", "Date": "on April 9, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "can't control my lights when my Internet connection is down", "Text": "bad product design - I can't control my nightstand lights when the Internet does not work (and that happens from time to time since my provider is Spectrum/Brighthouse)"}
{"Author": "NotMilk", "Date": "on April 8, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Only the beginning", "Text": "This has been a super fun journey for us. It is a treat to have my house say goodbye every day when I head to work :)"}
{"Author": "SJ Sena", "Date": "on April 8, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Highly recommend product.", "Text": "Excellent product. I'm sure you will be pleaded with the functionality of this product. I can't give 5 stars because I believe there is room for improvement with the Samsung Camera functions. Automation setup is a breeze. Device function such as switches, HVAC thermostat and motion detection work flawlessly. Keep the new devices comming. Highly recommended product."}
{"Author": "Teejay", "Date": "on April 7, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Automate my house", "Text": "Smart home the universal way. Many suported devices with a community to help you with devices not yet officially suported. There's one star missing because its a bit of a hassle to get all features from devices that aren't 100% functionally suported but they more than likely will work. If you've read this far then you may not mind creating another user name and password as a st developer to enter code from x user from such and such site that your required to log in with another password after a noninal fee ( typical). Once your smart home is set up you'll want more more more automation!!"}
{"Author": "Alfred Dookwah", "Date": "on April 7, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Very easy to setup and works well"}
{"Author": "Robert D", "Date": "on April 6, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great Samsung support", "Text": "Have used this for over a year. The major surprise was that I got a call back from technical support when I needed support to create a routine for a set of 9 led hue changing recessed lights. The tech gave me the head start needed to create it."}
{"Author": "JS", "Date": "on April 6, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works fine for lights", "Text": "We only use the hub for on-call smart light switches and smart light bulbs. It works flawlessly for those.\n\nI'd love to see easier widgets built in to control my light. A workaround for Android right now is a great app called sharptools."}
{"Author": "Dale Shell", "Date": "on April 6, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Has worked with no problems", "Text": "Quick setup next to my router upstairs and it works with devices which are all downstairs. I was scared to write a review saying how good it worked I didn't want to jinx it, but this has worked great. I thought I may need a second one, but so far no need."}
{"Author": "Laura B", "Date": "on April 6, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "As described"}
{"Author": "Jon Doe", "Date": "on April 5, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "You don't own me, Samsung does.", "Text": "You do not own Samsung products. Samsung owns them. You do not get to use them except in approved manners. You do not get to decide when it works and when it does not work. You do not get to decide when updates are applied. All of this information is hidden somewhere in their terms of service; but I have yet to be able to find it. This product doesn't work well with hue lights, IFTTT, iOS, or any other automation software or hardware that I've found."}
{"Author": "Trynyti", "Date": "on April 5, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works great with all our smart devices.", "Text": "Works great with all our Lutron switches, LIFX bulbs, outlets and the Schlage door lock. Very happy with the updated version."}
{"Author": "Verne Christensen", "Date": "on April 4, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Pretty sure this is the best hub on the market. So much custom code for almost any device."}
{"Author": "cg2", "Date": "on April 4, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Life changing, it's something you don't realize you need until you get it.", "Text": "Omg, where do I start. This is awesome. We use this to control our lights in our house. We did change light switches so they are compatible. We can control them thru voice with Amazon Echo or Dot or from our phone. Saving us on electric cost. Our teenagers are always leaving lights on and now while at work I can turn them off from my phone or tablet. We will be adding other devices to it in the future."}
{"Author": "Edwin", "Date": "on April 4, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Excellent recommend"}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on April 3, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Smart things not good for a alarm system", "Text": "The motion switches work sometimes the module plug-ins work sometime not reliable and the Wemo switches they pop in and out doesn't give correct indication of whether or not off or on not worth it right now"}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on April 3, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Four Stars", "Text": "works with the rite attachments"}
{"Author": "moe", "Date": "on April 3, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Works well I love it Wish there were more Gadgets to use with it."}
{"Author": "ZenDarb", "Date": "on April 2, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easy Set Up", "Text": "There is a lot to like about this system!\n1. EASY to set up. EASY.\n2. So many things (basically all the 'internet of things' type equipment) connects to it\n3. Did I say it was easy to set up?\n\nSo, why not 5 stars?\n\nBasically, the app. It is good, but needs improvement. Whenever there is an alert, you go to check the app and it takes a few seconds to refresh. Not a huge deal, but it gets a bit annoying after awhile.\n\nWe are still getting used to how the system works and fine tuning how the alarms trigger, but it really helps knowing what is going on in the home (using it primarily for security right now)."}
{"Author": "Steve L", "Date": "on March 31, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "works well"}
{"Author": "Andrew", "Date": "on March 30, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Beware of interference and low range", "Text": "Works well, mobile software is decent too for setting up schedules like at dusk or dawn or set times. Beware the Z wave protocol this uses will interfere with low frequency radio wave devices like babycams. Luckily my cams had multiple channels and after a little tinkering testing channels I was able to get smartthings working. Also note this has a fairly mediocre range. I strongly recommend using wifi devices such as wemo devices on wifi for better reliability."}
{"Author": "Irwin", "Date": "on March 30, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Four Stars", "Text": "Great product to start home automation with."}
{"Author": "Monty", "Date": "on March 30, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "It works, but has its flaws that I can live with", "Text": "First, it does work when I need it to as long as I have a strong signal wherever I am. I have had problems connecting with it when I have spotty cell phone service, but that is to be expected. Also, it does need to be within a reasonable proximity of the switches and outlets that it is controlling. I did have problems with connecting to a switch after the initial set up, but they were resolved when I moved the hub closer.\n\nThe options for interfacing with the Honeywell thermostats leave much to be desired. It seems like you can't change the schedule or make temporary temperature changes on the thermostat, but only permanent temperature changes. I only use the Honeywell app for adjusting my thermostats.\n\nThe biggest complaint that I have with this hub is that it loses connectivity several times per day. It seems to regain connectivity right away, but when it loses it, it causes a rapid flashing blue light on my phone which is annoying to see flash during the night. I have tried moving it in different places along with the router it is connected to, but this issue doesn't go away.\n\n**EDIT: After speaking with a rep from Smartthings, I have learned the connectivity issue that I've been having is with the Honeywell connectivity. It is still a Smartthings issue and not a Honeywell issue and they are supposed to be working on a fix for it. I will update my review accordingly once the fix has been applied."}
{"Author": "jnet", "Date": "on March 29, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great hub except for the backup battery issues", "Text": "I've been really pleased with the ST hub so far. The range is good - my devices are pretty scattered and the connection has been reliable. The Android app is good, but the iPad app it really needs some updating. Echo integration is surprisingly great.\n\nOne major issue - and this is well-documented - is the back up batteries. Mine died within two weeks of installation. I was lucky that my power went out and I got a notification the my hub was off-line, leading me to check the batteries and learn about this issue online. Many users end up with nasty, corroded batteries in their hub. Samsung seems to be silent on this issue. I ditched the backup batteries and used a POE extractor instead. It's powered by a remote UPS. Problem solved."}
{"Author": "ZT", "Date": "on March 28, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "owned product for a few months and have not experienced ...", "Text": "owned product for a few months and have not experienced any issues. Hub stays online and manages the reports well. I wish it was a little simpler to program routines when an action occurs"}
{"Author": "oldbaritone", "Date": "on March 28, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Pretty good, but not compatible with Lutron devices", "Text": "I like it overall, but it does not support Lutron dimmers unless you buy an additional Lutron hub and link to yet-another-cloud-account. My old Wink hub did support Lutron without buying another hub. I'm mostly happy, but disappointed that I had to replace a couple of incompatible devices which cost almost as much as the new hub. It's pretty good at finding Z-wave things and getting them set up. Functionality of the SmartThings app is good. I chose it because of \"best choice\" ratings in many reviews, but I might have chosen a different hub knowing what I know now. It does everything they say it will do."}
{"Author": "ISSAGA KANE", "Date": "on March 28, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great product.", "Text": "I was hesitating between the Wink and Smartthings. I'm glad i went with Smarthings. It is compatible with almost everything u can think off. The community is fantastic.\nI'm currently having a friend go with smartthings as well."}
{"Author": "Joshua K Friel", "Date": "on March 28, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "The fact that the hub has to be plugged into a wired Ethernet connection is a little constraining but I am much happier with the", "Text": "I upgraded from a 1st Gen. Wink Hub. The fact that the hub has to be plugged into a wired Ethernet connection is a little constraining but I am much happier with the performance."}
{"Author": "N. Zett", "Date": "on March 28, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Affordable, decent support, but wish it could work on a local network when internet is down.", "Text": "Works really well and has only lost it's config 1 time in several months of use. The only reason I don't give it 5 stars is that it seems like having the unit work on the local wifi network instead of having to go out to the internet would be more useful. If my internet goes out (common with Comcast), I cannot control my lights. If it would just work on the internal network as a primary or fallback, I could still have control of my lights even when the internet goes down."}
{"Author": "George", "Date": "on March 27, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Amazon Echo and Google Home compatible", "Text": "Decided to automate my house with the Amazon Echo. Then I was gifted an Google Home. These two devices although similar do not handle automation the same. The Samsung Smartthings hug will work with both these devices. The hub communicates with \"Z-Wave\" which is a very common communication between automation devices. Z-Wave is the only maker I have found for 3-way light switches. The hub will control many other devices such as bulbs, locks, switches, dimmers, sensors and more. I control the device through an app on my phone.\n\nPros: Works with universal Z-Wave technology. It can control 50+different devices. If placed in a central location has good range for my bedrooms. Takes only one TCPIP address. Other type of devices each take an address and communicate individually on the internet. Works both with Google and Amazon. Devices purchased for this hub cost generally less than those that talk directly to the internet. My guess they are simpler. The service that talks to Amazon and Google is free. Some have additional charges. This does not.\n\nCons: It will only control \"Z-wave\" compatible devices. I haven't found this much of a problem as more devices are being released all the time. Devices using this hub have limited intelligence. All the smarts is in the hub and the App from Samsung. Although the app is good, it does have some limitations. I have not found many."}
{"Author": "Z. Chen", "Date": "on March 27, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Terrible Outages!", "Text": "A North American outage status is being reported from the system as I am writing this review. What this means is that as a user, I am unable to communicate with my Smartthings system, check device statuses (including camera and sensors) for my home, disarm, or arm my home. Do not buy this system if you plan to use it for the security it offers. Often times it will leave you wondering what might be happening to your home while it is offline (as they figure out what is causing these outages.)\n\nWhen I first got the system for my home, and outages happened, I could understand because the system is still new, and they might need to iron out any kinks it might have. But it has been OVER A YEAR and outages happen once or twice weekly. A lot can be forgiven if the support and system is new, but this is UNACCEPTABLE. This product leaves me feeling uneasy and I do not have faith that it will alert me when or if my home is in danger. I will be trashing this system quite soon and switching to a better tried and tested system. Samsung taking on this company does not mean anything. I thought it would improve but sadly it has gotten much worse."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on March 27, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easy to inatsll and works great", "Text": "Easy to inatsll and works great."}
{"Author": "Tommy V", "Date": "on March 27, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great \"hub\" product to use with other samsung devices", "Text": "Great \"hub\" product to use with other samsung devices. Once you set this up, it's easy to add other receivers to use with your Alexa commands."}
{"Author": "Cory H.", "Date": "on March 27, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "alexa loves this.", "Text": "Works great with alexa. Interface is a little clunky. you have to login to your specific area's portal or you can't see what apps you have installed. other than that thought it works great."}
{"Author": "andy h", "Date": "on March 27, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "So far it is the best hub I have had. Just switched from vera edge.", "Text": "So far it is the best hub I have owned. I been with vera from the start. Always a nightmare to setup and takes days. My last was the vera edge. It went stupid on me for the last time it would not reset or update. I was tempted to but the next model think it is the plus but decide I was tired of messing with vera.\n\nAnd wanted to try something else now that there are several choices.\nI needed a hub the same day and found it on sale in local store the smartthings v2 I figured if I not like it I could return it. But I loved it it updated when I first hooked it up took about 15 min required nothing from me just adding it to my account on phone. I was able to exclude all my devices with the hub and had them all up and going in under a hr. Expect one multi sensor I had. But with little research I uploaded a custom device handler and it was up and going. So in most cases if it don't work out of the box someone has already made the code for the handler just google it copy and upload and you goog to go.\n\nSo far no problems. I live in a older rv. I have 2 older roof Acs I put 2 zwave relays on them and use my multi sensor to turn them on and off. I used there app that was on it already can set it to be one temp when no motion and if up and moving arround it will keep it at a diff temp if I want using the motion and temp sensor.\n\nI will stay with the smart things unless it ever gives me problems if hub ever goes out I will buy another. Easy to setup Home Secretary with it and plan on switching my camera system to the net gear arlo they work with the hub. If looking for a hub that just works with little effort get this.\n\nThe vera may have more options but there is nothing needed that smartthings won't do. And vera has to many bugs.\n\nThe smartthings work better for my engery moniters to"}
{"Author": "R. M. Silva", "Date": "on March 26, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Placement of this hub is KEY.", "Text": "I purchased this hub with 1 Leviton Z-wave switch and 2 Leviton Z-wave outlets, all placed in different parts of the house. I initially placed the SmartThings Hub in my entertainment unit, because I have an ethernet switch there. This was a BAD MOVE, because I had HUGE problems with electromagnetic interference. From there, I moved the hub to a bedroom, but nothing worked from that location. After 4 more moves around the house, I finally found a spot in the house that is 1) centrally located 2) away from metal and electronics and 3) within the proximity of a network connection.\n\nI was very close to returning the unit, but after finding the sweet spot, everything now works. The integration with Alexa works great. I really wish the unit were more powerful, so owners could have the flexibility to place the unit in more places around the house."}
{"Author": "Nic Rupert", "Date": "on March 25, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Amazingly functional and easy to setup your smart home with.", "Text": "This has changed the way we interact with our home. I will never be able to live in a dumb home again. How quickly you get used to being able to control things from your phone and with Alexa..."}
