{"Author": "Jamazon", "Date": "on March 23, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Very good, stable, easy to use hub that plays well with Alexa", "Text": "Pro:\nVery stable,\neasy initial setup. Easy to connect my Zwave switches to it.\nIntigrates easily with Amazon Echo/Alexa.\nSmarthings App is easy to use, but for some reason mis-reports z-wave PLUS switches sometimes as on, when they are off. It still controls it, but if I'm not in front of the light to see it, I have to cycle the light off-on-off, via the app, to be sure it is off because of the mis-report. I've rebooted the hub and no improvement on it. Slightly annoying since I like using the app, not just Alexa.\nI like the automation permitted so I can turn on/off multiple devices with one command when they are connected through this hub.\n\nCon:\nautomation is limited in complexity. I have it set to turn on my garage light when I come home (cool that it recognizes when my phone rejoins the home network. But there is no way to program it to delay an action (i.e. turn off garage light 10 minutes after I arrive)."}
{"Author": "Flashpoint I.", "Date": "on March 23, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great interface, limited functionality", "Text": "The box and interface are very slick, but devices do not reliably trigger from automations. Without reliable automation, the device is basically useless."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on March 22, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I originally bought it for fun and to pair it with my Echo dot", "Text": "I have been using SmartThings for over a month now and it has been a very reliable product. I originally bought it for fun and to pair it with my Echo dot. i then add a few smart switches and just kept going. i have my whole first floor lights and outdoor lights connected to the hub. I have my outside lights set to com on at sunset and to go off at sunrise. I plan on adding a smart thermostat and door locks in the next few weeks. Great product."}
{"Author": "John G.", "Date": "on March 22, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Great system"}
{"Author": "Beth B. Bales", "Date": "on March 22, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Super happy with the hub", "Text": "Love this hub. I use it with the Amazon Echo. Very reliable and consistent. It controls the lights quickly. I have outlets and lightbulbs. It has not come unpaired at all in the few weeks I've owned it. It connects directly to the router and looks good. I've never had to do anything with it since the initial set up. Thumbs up. I look forward to finding new fun things to control with it."}
