{"Author": "Dennis", "Date": "on February 13, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Another Samsung product with battery issues", "Text": "Another Samsung product with battery issues. I purchased a brand new hub and less than 2 months later all the batteries have leaked inside the hub. This product takes hours to add devices and set up different rules. There is no way to move the rules and devices to a replacement hub.\n\nWaste of time and money."}
{"Author": "BoB W.", "Date": "on February 13, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "... of the easiest ways to get a lot of Smart home devices connected", "Text": "One of the easiest ways to get a lot of Smart home devices connected. Mobile app could use some usability work, but it's definitely a good starter product. I've only had it a few months, but it likely will be a good product for a long time to come considering how much they've invested in a developer community around the SmartThings product line. I've been able to hook up most items (Philips Hue, motion detectors, contact switches, wall switches, plugs) with out any problems, but after a few dozen devices, the mobile app is a little more awkward to navigate then it should be."}
{"Author": "J. Watts", "Date": "on February 12, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "This is the future."}
{"Author": "JJ", "Date": "on February 12, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "really love this product more so works with Alexa"}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on February 12, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Works great."}
{"Author": "Roger", "Date": "on February 12, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works with Google Home", "Text": "Great light/device controller. Also connects to Google Home and controls Sylvanya OSRAM A19 RGBW lights."}
{"Author": "Greg A", "Date": "on February 11, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I love the Samsung SmartThings", "Text": "I love the Samsung SmartThings. I started out with the Logitech Harmony Elite for control of my entertainment system and added Phillips Hue bridge and lights. Wanted to control my Garage Door and found out Harmony with the extender hub couldn't control my Z-Wave garage door opener I purchased but that SmartThings did so I bought the SmartThings hub. Added Alexa to the mix with all the skills and am loving the SmartHome automation. It will be an ongoing project over the next year."}
{"Author": "Matthew Mehlich", "Date": "on February 11, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "This 2nd Gen hub has worked flawlessly for me with around 25 Z-Wave devices attached"}
{"Author": "Brad C.", "Date": "on February 10, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Best hub available", "Text": "Best hub available, did a lot of research. Great app and love the Google Home integration"}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on February 10, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "One Star", "Text": "Very disappointed....many false alarms."}
{"Author": "Videotechman", "Date": "on February 10, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Smart thing Hub", "Text": "A must to voice activate your Google home network endpoints."}
{"Author": "Crabber", "Date": "on February 10, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Really a straight forward way to automate your home", "Text": "It takes a bit of effort to get an understanding of Pairing/Unpairing devices, setting up routines etc. but once done it works exceptionally well."}
{"Author": "Scott Rowe", "Date": "on February 9, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Exactly as described. Works great"}
{"Author": "S. Robinson", "Date": "on February 9, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "This is the \"brains\" of any home automation setup."}
{"Author": "Lucy Cleland", "Date": "on February 9, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Love it"}
{"Author": "nathan", "Date": "on February 8, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Beware! $$$$", "Text": "Beware! you may become addicted to automating your home. With all the things that connect to this device, you might go broke, but you're going to have so much fun along the way. I personally use Alexa, but there are other options. with the online programming options, customization, and a large support base, the possibilities will make you crazy."}
{"Author": "thatdamnhoney", "Date": "on February 8, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Good, so far.", "Text": "So far having minimum problems with set ups. I have some issue with using a phone as a presence sensor, but the hub itself has only gone offline once for a few minutes. However, there seemed to be power problems in our area that night. The hub hasn't let me down yet."}
{"Author": "aujbman", "Date": "on February 8, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "App and Hub together = greatness", "Text": "Great center piece for your Home Automation.\n\nI have this in my spare room connected to the router. Currently, it controls three lights in different rooms in the house. I also had IFTTT and Stringify on my phone to help out with the automation. Once you link those to your Smartthings account, you are off and running. I was pleased to find out, though, that the smartthings app actually has pretty decent ability to automate things on its own without any third party apps.\n\nFor example, the smartthings (st) app will know when you are home by sensing your phone connected to the wifi. Therefore, it can turn on your lights when you arrive at home and turn them off when you leave. I used to have an IFTTT recipe for this but it became unreliable. The st app fires everytime and when I had it attached to a Stringify recipe (they call them flows) sometimes I could see my lights come on from the street before I turned into the driveway. (Pretty awesome to see.)\n\nI have never had any problem connecting anything so far and everything has just simply worked well connected to this hub. I also have a Harmony hub connected as well. I will leave a review on that as well."}
{"Author": "Dave D", "Date": "on February 8, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great product", "Text": "I am using this to control 4 lights in my condo. Works well with Amazon Dot/Alexa."}
{"Author": "Richard H. Van Cleave", "Date": "on February 8, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Worth the purchase price", "Text": "Easy to install, works with Google Home,"}
{"Author": "Rachel", "Date": "on February 8, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love it!", "Text": "This item is great! We are very happy with it and the ability to add items to it. We did a lot of research on these types of products, this one was the best that we found that would allow us to add other products to it. We are very pleased."}
{"Author": "S. Council", "Date": "on February 7, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Reboot early, reboot often.", "Text": "Reboot weekly, along with all of your smart home stuff. This technology is in its adolescence and a regular flush and drain works wonders with keeping everything \"kind-of\" connected.\n\nNote: Before blaming the ST hub, Google your device(s) that have the most problems. Reboot them as well."}
{"Author": "Grant Rudolph", "Date": "on February 7, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Had a hard time maintaining connections with my Z-Wave devices and lacked the ability to really customize scenes and individual", "Text": "This just wasn't for me, unfortunately. Had a hard time maintaining connections with my Z-Wave devices and lacked the ability to really customize scenes and individual devices like codes for the door lock."}
{"Author": "James", "Date": "on February 7, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "My smart things hub is awesome it's worth the money thank ...", "Text": "My smart things hub is awesome it's worth the money thank you smart things"}
{"Author": "Quince", "Date": "on February 6, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I like it so much", "Text": "Excellent"}
{"Author": "Stanley W.", "Date": "on February 6, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Amazing system"}
{"Author": "Curtain Call", "Date": "on February 6, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I feel like I am a Pro", "Text": "I have it connected to the Z-Wave Mimolite module and Curtain Call Electric Curtain System. It works seamlessly !\nThe SmartThings Hub picks up the device in 20 seconds! And the set up was so user friendly! I feel like I am a Pro :) even it is my first time doing it. It also works with Amazon Echo !!! Now I can tell Alexa to open or close my curtain !! The experience is wonderful! This is a great Hub!"}
{"Author": "fercho", "Date": "on February 6, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "lo que siempre buscaba", "Text": "Finally I can automatize my home , I love it,"}
{"Author": "ECA", "Date": "on February 5, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great hub with some minor issues.", "Text": "This hub is better than other z-wave hubs I have used. I have had some things that I am trying to resolve. I scheduled a z-wave outlet to turn off at midnight. Sometimes the lights turn off and sometimes they don't. I am trying to determine what the problem is. Otherwise it works great,"}
{"Author": "Dwayne Dickie", "Date": "on February 5, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "I just love what I can do with this hub."}
{"Author": "THall", "Date": "on February 5, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Great product"}
{"Author": "gary", "Date": "on February 5, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works as advertised", "Text": "Works as advertised"}
{"Author": "Joel", "Date": "on February 4, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Come for the convenience, stay for the community!", "Text": "So far so good. Hub's been up for about a month and a half now and I'm just getting into some serious exploration - having some fun with community created apps and such. The community is really what sets this product apart. They are helpful, responsive, generative and patient. The ST devs often show up in the threads, too, which is pretty cool for a major market device. The Echo Dot is what got me into this new Home Automation/Smart Home craze and I've really been enjoying it (though my pocketbook is considerably lighter for all the fun I've been having). Grab you a hub, sign in to the forums and join us!"}
{"Author": "Pepperfly", "Date": "on February 4, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works great! No problem setting up", "Text": "Works great! No problem setting up."}
{"Author": "Jayne Owen Parker", "Date": "on February 4, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "This product is worthless with an iphone, support is non-existent, a total waste of money.", "Text": "There is nothing smart about this product. The app does not work -- will not recognize the \"Welcome Code\" that ca e box. The link to the support mailbox will not work and if you try to send email address the get support you receive a message saying that the email box is bein repaired. This does not work with an iphone at all."}
{"Author": "not Mark Twain", "Date": "on February 4, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "It mated to the Fibaro flood sensor like a champ", "Text": "This Hub has worked flawlessly for the last 5 months. It mated to the Fibaro flood sensor like a champ. This is the wave of the future"}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on February 4, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "SmartThings hub", "Text": "SmartThings Hub Works. I have lights, temp (ecobee), motion sensors, garage opener. So far. I plan to add more."}
{"Author": "Bankdude1", "Date": "on February 4, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Very limited hub transmit range [Max 20-25 feet]", "Text": "After I researched many of the Smart Home Hubs available on Amazon, I chose SmartThings, based upon the glowing reviews. After receiving my hub and setting it up (Very easy to do!) sadly, the SmartThings hub's optimum transmit range is limited to about 20-25 feet. This is great if you live in an apartment, but if you live in a house like I do, ALL of your switches, receptacles and controllers MUST be within a maximum of a 20-25 foot arc from the hub, otherwise they will not receive their signal from the hub and properly work!!!\n\nTech support was fantastic!!! You could not get better assistance! They know their product! After 2.5 hours chatting with them and using a 50 foot Ethernet cable to move the SmartThings hub closer to the light switches to pair them, we discovered that even after they were added to the hub and it was placed back in its place next to the router, the hub could not reach the wall switches to control them.\n\nIt appears that my only option now is to purchase a Z-Wave MESH Network Extender to see if that will work with the GE Z-Wave brand products. Perhaps the Z-Wave technology is also contributing to my challenge with the GE receptacles, switches, fan controllers and dimmers, which I purchased to work with my SmartThings hub. I do not know for sure...\n\nThere is no way that the SmartThings Hub can control a regular 'whole house' as depicted in their advertisements in combination with GE Z-Wave products. The idea is great, but unless the FCC or whomever allows them to goose up the transmit power of the hub to increase its range, it is limited to just a few rooms in your home which are closest to the hub."}
{"Author": "Sebastiano Cancellieri", "Date": "on February 4, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Love it...."}
{"Author": "Scott P.", "Date": "on February 3, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "poor connectivity. wish it would hook up with wifi", "Text": "poor connectivity. wish it would hook up with wifi, frequently does not recognize all components of smart home and has stated with security system that all components are working, when in fact they were not. a door contact was opened and the alarm did not go off and software stated that the battery life was OK and it was closed when in fact it was not closed. Very poor if you want to rely on it for a security system monitoring doors and windows. i have a motion sensor and it has an internal temperature monitor which i wanted to use to monitor the temperature of my lake cabin which is set at 45 in winter and it is reading 70's/ for a samsung product i feel this product has many flaws. hopefully upgrades are coming"}
{"Author": "Shife", "Date": "on February 3, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Unreliable cloud processing", "Text": "Continuous issues with connectivity to their cloud processing. Completely unreliable. This is basically a beta product and they expect their customers to be guinea pigs. If you are expecting a consumer ready product that will reliably automate the operation of a switch, look elsewhere."}
{"Author": "Jimmie Stewart", "Date": "on February 3, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Type of support is a problem", "Text": "Support is literally at your fingertips, that in itself is a major part of the problem. In order to communicate it must be through a computer or smart phone. It is much better when problems can be discussed verbally from one human to another, provided they both clearly speak the same language. A support telephone number would be great. If the problem isn't resolved soon my support of the hub will be terminated. To date there are at least 6 hubs that were purchased through my recommendation."}
{"Author": "G. Hunt", "Date": "on February 2, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Good hub but...", "Text": "Disappointed it does not work with a Samsung Smart TV"}
{"Author": "D", "Date": "on February 2, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Awesome", "Text": "Wow, what a breath of fresh air!! A hub that actually works the first time! If your trying to decide between this hub and the Insteon hub, than take my advice and go with Samsung. Installation process is very easy, and works well with Alexa! I had the hub along with multiple devices working within minutes.No problems."}
{"Author": "Gerry", "Date": "on February 2, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "If it worked as designed I'd love it. It doesn't", "Text": "If it worked as designed I'd love it. It doesn't. Pairing items is a pain in the butt every time. Times events don't happen, which appears to be a bug for a year and a half. The app doesn't refresh properly so sometimes you have to close it and reopen. Sadly I didn't keep the original packaging so I can't return it otherwise I would."}
{"Author": "Matt", "Date": "on February 2, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Not necessary for most devices", "Text": "I don't see the point. It doesn't work with most Samsung Smart TVs (huge oversight). And you don't need it for most smart lighting or outlets (most bulbs and sockets now work directly with Alexa or phone apps without needing a hub). So basically this is a fancy, expensive way to control smart devices that (for the most part) can integrate without an intermediary by just using a phone app."}
{"Author": "Spike M.", "Date": "on February 2, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "yep works for me"}
{"Author": "John R.", "Date": "on February 1, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Greta product which has wide z-wave support", "Text": "very easy to set up and has a wide range of compatibility with smart products. Great for adding z-wave on top of the Philips Hue hub stuff which was kind of one-dimensional (ZigBee)"}
{"Author": "The Net Doctor", "Date": "on February 1, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love the wide range of 3rd party device support", "Text": "Love the wide range of 3rd party device support, the ability to create my own custom smart apps, and that it is rock solid stable. I used wemo before and my devices were off line more than online. Having devices relay allowed me to cover areas I could not get reception in before.\nAlso I love the fact that you can access the code from all the premade smart apps so you can use them as a template to make your own custom ones."}
{"Author": "Merv Martin", "Date": "on February 1, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "I'm having a blast automating"}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on February 1, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Quick and easy", "Text": "Quick and easy to set up. Works well and has a good app."}
{"Author": "Drew B", "Date": "on January 31, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Powerful and easy to use."}
{"Author": "The Man", "Date": "on January 31, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "this hub is superior then VeraLite and easy to setup and use", "Text": "After having Vera Lite for a couple of years, this hub is superior then VeraLite and easy to setup and use. I was able to move everything I had on Vera to Smartthing with a couple of problems, but they were easy to resolve using the community blog.\n\nThe only problems I would see issue with is using the 4 scene/zone wall controller from Leviton without using the Leviton programming tool.\n\nI'm only 1 month in and so far the response of the hub is very fast. I have about 70+ devices (mixed brand of Z-WAVE devices, from cheap to expensive) connected to the hub and everything works accordingly. To move all the devices and create routines/automation schedules from Vera to Smarthings, it took entire weekend. Afterwards I have been adding addition features I did not have on Vera yet, such as Alexa, Harmony,Geofencing (Was on Vera but didn't work correctly for me), and Cameras (Arlo).\n\nOverall I'm very happy with the product!"}
{"Author": "CaryKings", "Date": "on January 31, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easy to setup and good price.", "Text": "This device is easy to setup and it integrates well with Amazon Echo (Alexa) I can easily control lights with verbal commands using Alexa, and I have several scheduled events to turn lights on in the morning to wake us up, and in the evening to make sure our house has a lived in look."}
{"Author": "Slyescokat", "Date": "on January 31, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Very easy to setup and works as it should", "Text": "Very easy to setup and works as it should. I love the fact that I can control and monitor my smartthings from the outside. Also I can setup up a gentle wake up in the morning with my lights which mimics the sunrise."}
{"Author": "Mike", "Date": "on January 30, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Works well. Using as a secondary controller for my Elk M1 interface."}
{"Author": "H.S.M.", "Date": "on January 30, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Included AA backup batteries leaked and destroyed circuit board", "Text": "Bought it on September 2016. Now it is January 2017 and the four Rayovac AA backup batteries that were included leaked a white powdery dust into the internal circuits of the Smartthings corroding the internal circuit board making unusable because now it doesn't even startup.\nPoor design concerning the protection of internal circuit board againt battery leaking only after 5 months of having the 4 included batteries inserted in the memory backup compartment of the Smartthings.\nIs there any warranty/replacement on this from Amazon ? I used the included AA batteries and it should have lasted at least about 1 year without leakage. It was sold to me by Amazon, LLC\nI planned to purchase an Echo Dot to pair with this device and now I am left out with nothing to control other zwave devices.\n\nUpdate (February 24 2017):\nContacted Samsung Customer Service by chat and sent them the pictures of leaked batteries and corroded battery springs as proof and they kindly agreed to send me a replacement hub as it was still covered by warranty. I am happy by their customer support. Their engineers just need to redesign the battery compartmens in order to separate the batteries from the circuit boards. Upgraded this review from 1 star to 4 stars."}
{"Author": "Betty", "Date": "on January 29, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Does a great job and an easy set up"}
{"Author": "Daniel Grayson", "Date": "on January 29, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "great product. Interface a little hard to get use to but once you do it works great! Love it..", "Text": "great product. Interface a little hard to get use to but once you do it works great! Love it.."}
{"Author": "Puhi Niho", "Date": "on January 29, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Four Stars", "Text": "Great product but wish it was easier to use/understand and more interoperability with other smart devices."}
{"Author": "John J. Gartin", "Date": "on January 29, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Excellent!", "Text": "Everything I expected + more!"}
{"Author": "Lord Vader", "Date": "on January 29, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "The Best Home Automation Hub Available", "Text": "Got it for 50 bucks when Amazon had them on sale, and the quickly started adding home automation bulbs, switches, and a home-made garage door opener to the system. Integrated well with both Alexa (full size Echo and a Dot) and Google Home, though Alexa understands the commands a lot better, and easier, than Google Home does. To be fair though, the Alexa devices are away from external noise sources while the Google Home is pretty close to the TV.\n\nHaven't run into anything I couldn't connect; LED bulbs from several different manufacturers, a variety of switches and dimmers, and even made some custom scripts for customized control of different things. If you're looking to get into home automation, I think Smart Things is the way to go. Works well and there is a plethora of support and third-party apps available to work with it."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on January 29, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great value and works as it should.", "Text": "Works as described. Easy setup. Stays connected all the time. App is super easy to operate."}
{"Author": "GrizzleBox", "Date": "on January 28, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easy to install", "Text": "Easy to install, works great with all Samsung SmartThings devices.\n\nWould had been 5 star except the app takes a little bit to configure and fully understand to be able to do detailed routines. Also, my current switches appears to still in the in \"Samsung Lab\" for testing.\n\nWill revisit a 5 star review when I see a bit more cross compatibility options."}
{"Author": "John C. Porter", "Date": "on January 28, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "If I could return it I would but at his point it is going in the trash", "Text": "Totally disappointed with this product and would never recommend this to anyone. The only device this works with is my thermostat. Purchased some smart lights and set the automation and the lights would go on and off when they decided to. Bought a Sonos Speaker (Which I Love) and could not connect to it (Samsungs response was this product id not fully tested however they have a full webpage on how to connect to it)\nCustomer Support was a waste of time as all they did was read the manual back to me.\n\nI was a big supporter of Samsung, but this has really left a bad taste in my mouth"}
{"Author": "J. Waits", "Date": "on January 28, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Really easy to use, works with a wide variety of devices."}
{"Author": "Reginald Holloway", "Date": "on January 27, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Best thing since slice bread"}
{"Author": "MikeRigel", "Date": "on January 27, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "... frequently drops but I have had nothing but a good experience since I've set it up", "Text": "I was a little hesitant to purchase this because of the negative reviews and reports that the device frequently drops but I have had nothing but a good experience since I've set it up. I recommend this product and I would buy it again."}
{"Author": "Jeffrey S. King", "Date": "on January 27, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Runs the house..", "Text": "Love it. Works well with my ecobee thermostat, Cree, Hue, and GE Devices. Easy to use, and intuitive. It's my favorite of the hubs, and since purchasing this device for use with Alexa and google home devices, I seldom use the native hue app. The ecosphere of apps that come with it, make it worth its weight in gold."}
{"Author": "Hank", "Date": "on January 27, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Easy to set up and use. Dependable."}
{"Author": "Richard N.", "Date": "on January 27, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great to just be able to plug and play", "Text": "Works exactly as advertised. Great to just be able to plug and play!"}
{"Author": "Paul", "Date": "on January 27, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "No support for Windows", "Text": "Although advertised as working and support for Windows products, that is ending. Do not buying if you plan to use with Windows Phones or other devices."}
{"Author": "P. Brinkley", "Date": "on January 27, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Nice Hub", "Text": "Purchased this hub for a Philips Hue BR30 light bulb and some smart electrical outlets. It works great. I have another hub which I was using for other smart devices in my home but this one works great too. The setup was incredibly easy and intuitive and it works with my echo. I am glad I tried this hub"}
{"Author": "Rachel", "Date": "on January 26, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "So happy I went with a smart home!", "Text": "Love this, can't believe I wen this long w/out a smart home! Easy to set up and connect, stays connected, nice selection of compatible devices. Only gave it 4 stars because 1. Only has a mobile app, cannot use with a computer or tablet. GET A WEBSITE OR APP FOR A PC! 2. Mobile app crashes and logs me out ALL THE TIME! I have had to restart the app more times than I can count because it freezes, and I have to log back in 99% of the time I open the app, sometimes even after I just used it. I have my home security through Scout and the hub. Going to switch because the lack of ability to control alarm except through the mobile app, and with it not opening properly or having to log in means the alarm goes off ALOT! Plus, if I lose my phone I have no way to turn off the alarm system, and if the internet goes down, so does my alarm system. But as far as using with lights, ect, I am very happy. I connected to an Amazon Echo so I now have voice control over lights! Motion sensors work great most of the time, but get a little squirrely even now and them. Looking to add water leak sensors. Wish is had more native compatibility with devices rather than using IFTTT, and worked better with Schlage locks. Really glad I went to a smart home, will never go back."}
{"Author": "Martin Allen Fisker", "Date": "on January 26, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Very pleased with your actions"}
{"Author": "Learner123", "Date": "on January 26, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Less than I expected.", "Text": "So far not impressed. Smart things app has very slow response ( yes I have a fast internet connection). The hub arrived but smells like chemical fabric softener or something. Missing the LAN cable. Also, my WeMo won't connect! Sigh...."}
{"Author": "JohnnyF", "Date": "on January 26, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Amazing home automation that anyone can install", "Text": "Has worked great. Couldn't be happier, easy to set up. I have Cameras, smart switches, garage door opener, door monitors all hooked up and they all work seamlessly."}
