{"Author": "Alan Edwards", "Date": "on January 25, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Yeah!!! Works with Schlage door locks!", "Text": "Love it as I finally got something to work to lock and unlock my Schlage door lock. I can now unlock my door remotely with the iPhone app which is great. It also connects to Samsung Smart cameras"}
{"Author": "Robin L Southwood", "Date": "on January 25, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Great performance. Simple set up"}
{"Author": "Daniel", "Date": "on January 25, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "RELIABLE SYSTEM BUT COMPLICATED", "Text": "I've used the smartthings hub and the wink hub as well. While the wink hub is more glitchy and less reliable I feel the smarthings is very complicated to use. The mobile app interface in my opinion is not very easy to navigate. There is a collection of devices that are pre-configured in the system which makes it easy to pair those devices but it seems they are more geared towards the smarthings devices. The system is a open system which allows you to add a very large number of third party devices and integrate them all together using one system. This is good for someone like me who has multiple systems but this mostly needs to be done though their Web Portal. And to do this you need to almost have coding knowledge or hope another member has already pre-configured this before. Personally I prefer wink over smartthings. The user interface is a lot more easier and user friendly."}
{"Author": "ArtinTampa", "Date": "on January 25, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Very Intuitive", "Text": "I have owned this hub for over a year. At first, it was 'ok'. They have done several updates and now the hub is fantastic. It is my house's central nervous system. It has allowed me to automate doors, lights, TV's etc. I use it with Echo (Alexa), IFTTT and LIFX light bulbs. The three together make a great team. It knows when I leave the house (sometimes there's a delay but not usually bad) and sets the house/security system accordingly and does the same when I arrive."}
{"Author": "Steven I.", "Date": "on January 24, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Easy to get started and works great!", "Text": "Everything I expected and nothing I didn't. It was easy to get it working and adding devices was a cinch."}
{"Author": "Thomas T. Holtz", "Date": "on January 24, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works great and very easily connects to all kinds of sensors.", "Text": "Works great and very easily connects to all kinds of sensors. The App works well and always shows me the correct status and gives me alerts that I have set up."}
