{"Author": "Fidel a venado galicia", "Date": "on January 24, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "It Work excellent."}
{"Author": "wwilson", "Date": "on January 24, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "A+"}
{"Author": "Reesie", "Date": "on January 24, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Pretty Impressed!", "Text": "Out of the box review:\n\nI spent weeks going back and forth between this and the wink 2 hub and ultimately settled on this one because it just seemed like it could do more. Out of the box, this was extremely easy to set up. I have a lock, thermostat, echo (and two dots), and my garage door connected and each took seconds to pair with the hub. I love that this works with Alexa, although I have to familiarize myself more with the phrases before I can thoroughly review that part of the hub.\n\nOverall, I am very pleased with my purchase. I feel it was a great value for all that it can do and look forward to purchasing more home automation devices to pair with this. I will update after a few months to give a more substantial review!"}
{"Author": "cheers", "Date": "on January 23, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Smart Stuff!", "Text": "Love the flexibility of this product and the long list of products with which it provides compatibility."}
{"Author": "Fereesh", "Date": "on January 23, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Great product, connects everything I need"}
{"Author": "LHeath", "Date": "on January 23, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great home automation product!", "Text": "I bought this to work with Google Home and have been very happy with the product. Easy setup and it has worked flawlessly."}
{"Author": "Kwalls007", "Date": "on January 22, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "There are a few features I think this smart home system is missing", "Text": "There are a few features I think this smart home system is missing. First and foremost, it needs some sort of Admin control on the account. Without that, other users in the household can change anything they want. Secondly, it needs better support for Liftmaster Garage door openers. I purchased it after reading online that Lift Master planned to support it in the near future. But now I'm reading this is not looking to be very likely to happen anytime soon. Being this is probably the most widely used garage door opener company, this addition would be HUGE."}
{"Author": "James Andre", "Date": "on January 22, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "DO NOT INSTALL BATTERIES", "Text": "I actually bought the hub as a bundle but would like to warn everyone about battery leakage. The device will drain batteries quickly and will result in the batteries discharging and eventually corrode. This actually ended up cause my device that I got Nov 2016 to stop working on jan 2017. I am getting a replacement because I love the functionality. I will never install batteries in the new device!!!!!!!!!"}
{"Author": "Terry A.", "Date": "on January 22, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Works well"}
{"Author": "Eric G.", "Date": "on January 21, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Seamless integration with no headaches", "Text": "Have been pleasantly surprised with how well this has worked. It worked right out of the box and I've been able to add several GE smart dimmer switches to it and a linear go control garage door opener and everything has worked seamlessly. It's rare that a tech upgrade goes this smoothly for me. I didn't do a ton of homework on this before buying it but I'm thrilled with it so far."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on January 21, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Good solid product.", "Text": "Worked as advertised out of the box. Integration to Google Home was easy."}
{"Author": "cdsraines", "Date": "on January 21, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "YES INDEED", "Text": "after trying 4 other hubs and returning each this one is a keeper. love it but think the lack of PC software is a bummer but I found it easy to overlook after some time and the discovery of the API graph. Samsung creates this product with the DYI type and those who enjoy the ability to customize and create additional functionality in mind. While still remaining viable for the typical end user as well. With the best variety of protocols supported most smart home desires and needs are easily met."}
{"Author": "T. Smith", "Date": "on January 20, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Fantastic - while it worked.", "Text": "I used to be a SmartThings believer... until 7 weeks ago (the first week in December 2016) a cloud outage and/or firmware bug left the Hubs of many users \"in the cold\" and \"in the dark\", quite literally. ST's first tier support team has been extremely pleasant but even the support agents admit that their engineering team is not taking the problem seriously.\n\nSeveral dozen of us on the community boards have pooled our resources, spent many hours (possibly dozens to hundreds when you add up all the time spent) and tracked the issue to ST cloud-based processing. The affected hubs are both v1 and v2 and are being used with multiple network router brands, so it is fairly easy to identify the issue being a cloud or firmware issue.\n\nThe group of users on the community forums have had no success in getting restarted and are moving away from the SmartThings platform because of the lack of interest in fixing the users with broken service. Support wants to send us new hubs, but spending 4 days of removing devices from the old one manually and then manually associating them with the new one and building back all the automation rules I have built up over the past year or so is not my idea of a fun weekend... and support acknowledges, there is no guarantee that will even work.\n\nThen, this week, ST publicly admitted to another recent firmware update adversely affecting batteries in a way that makes them leak all over the inside of the unit. I checked my batteries and found the same issue, so now I have a hub gets cut off from the cloud, with an alkaline mess all over the table it is sitting on.\n\nApparently there is not much interest in the engineering side of the house in responding quickly to these issues - and 7+ weeks without a home automation system that relies on the cloud is a very long time. Today I spent my day looking into other alternatives and am sad to have to say goodbye to SmartThings. The product was great while it worked."}
{"Author": "Richard Greene", "Date": "on January 20, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "One Star", "Text": "support is poor, it works OK fro now. future unknown."}
{"Author": "Martin Chettle", "Date": "on January 20, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "home of the future for less than $100 bucks!", "Text": "home of the future for less than $100 bucks!"}
