{"Author": "Johnny S", "Date": "on January 20, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Dont throw away your money!", "Text": "I wanted this to work! I really did. It has been such a failure. Back and forth with their techs for months have yielded no satisfactory results. This is a total waste of money."}
{"Author": "Manuel Alonzo", "Date": "on January 19, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "A lot to be desired...", "Text": "Samsung needs to catch up with the other companies, Wink, Inteon, GE, to make more products connect in a foolproof way to this hub. I have tried several products that couldn't connect to it: the Cree light bulb, the Pivot Power Genius. MyQ Garage door opener used to connect to it , but not anymore. If you want to be adventurous you can try to connect other devices like the Ring doorbell with the help of the community forum, not Samsung tech support. Samsung only support 2 cameras and its own brand of camera has been hacked. I'd like their app to be more clear about the level of difficulty and resources needed to connect the devices they claim in their Marketplace tab. The literature claims the hub is Zwave and ZigBee compliant but it's not 100% applicable. There is still a lot to be desired about SmartThings."}
{"Author": "R. Thomas", "Date": "on January 19, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "There are better or wait till they establish smart home standards.", "Text": "Lacks compatibility. Not sure why it gets rated so well. I returned it."}
{"Author": "DoubleG", "Date": "on January 19, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Stay Away if you want multiple locations", "Text": "Does not work for multiple locations, it is just about impossible to change or remove a setup.\nIf you had only one location then it might work fine. the keychain sensors do not work at all."}
{"Author": "Doug", "Date": "on January 19, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Working good. Have it paired with 2 Lowe's Iris contact ...", "Text": "Working good. Have it paired with 2 Lowe's Iris contact sensors and one Lowe's Iris water sensor. Had a little trouble pairing it up at first, but after removing batteries and power from the hub for a reset, everything worked great."}
{"Author": "David E. Rominger", "Date": "on January 19, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "This item requires a phone in order to do anything ...", "Text": "This item requires a phone in order to do anything. You can't even create and account without a phone. You can't do the initial setup without a phone. You can't get started in any way without a phone. I have a phone...but I don't want to be TOTALLY reliant on it for the operation of anything that I own. So, I had to send this device back. A simple website where I could have set up an account would have been enough for me to keep this item."}
{"Author": "Ramster", "Date": "on January 18, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great functionality, device compatibility and easy to setup.", "Text": "Brilliant. I fully automated the home in just a couple weeks. I never expected to do that, but this controller was so easy to use, and the functionality so cool when paired with Alexa on Amazon echo or dot. I ended up replacing close to 30 outlets, light switches and fan switches. Now, we're saving electricity, lights turn on when we drive up to the house at night. I can shut off the porch, driveway, and yard lights from one switch or my phone. If I'm holding the baby in the nursery I can say, \"Alexa turn on nursery lights to 15%\" enough light to put her down and escape without tripping on a toy. This is only a hub, so only the start of your investment in automating the home. Before investing make sure all your compatible devices will work. Must electrical will need the neutral wire!"}
{"Author": "spufmeister", "Date": "on January 18, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "arrived promptly and as described"}
{"Author": "Ricky MaGloire", "Date": "on January 18, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Great everyone should have one."}
{"Author": "Rob Stewart", "Date": "on January 18, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "It works without issue and that is great!", "Text": "I bought this on black Friday deal for 50% off. Works great and have had no issues, disruptions, disconnects, etc. I would buy it again without any questions. If I don't have to mess with it, it's doing its' job."}
{"Author": "Kindle Customer", "Date": "on January 18, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "FRUSTRATION!", "Text": "I own this, along with a range of connected products, switches, motion sensors, alarms, light bulbs, the usual. I've had it for about a year now. It connects to a crapload of things, which is great. There are two rather-significant downsides, though: You ABSOLUTELY WILL be required to spend a lot of time in frustration, figuring out the app, and its connection to the devices. You LIKELY WILL be required to occasionally delete and reconnect the devices. You should DEFINITELY NOT rely on SmartThings for anything that actually matters. Use it for remote control, but not automation. It's just not THAT reliable.\n\nI got this response SOME TIME AGO from SmartThings, but it looks like it was removed? and I really wanted to reply to it:\n\"SmartThings Support says:\nHello, Ellen with SmartThings support here.\nI'm very sorry to hear you've had these reliability problems using SmartThings. I'd definitely like the chance to look into these issues that keep popping up to make sure we're doing everything we can to help. I completely understand the frustration of devices or the app failing to work as expected and I want to be sure to look into those problems in detail. If you find that you often need to remove and reconnect a device over and over, it's very likely that the device is on the edge of the Hub's range or is being affected by interference. Sometimes one small change like moving your Hub to a raised and open area a few feet away from the Router will make a huge difference in how well your devices stay connected. I'd really like the chance to...\"\n\nAnyway, since then I finally bought a 50' cat5 cable and placed the hub in the middle of the house. A couple of weeks later, now, the kitchen door just dropped off again. The kitchen door is about 18 feet away and is almost directly in the line of sight. Also, the Cree bulbs that I have (which a rep has told me, incidentally should not have a strong WIFI signal since they use ZigBee) still operate like crap."}
{"Author": "Steve", "Date": "on January 17, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Get A Vera Controller Instead", "Text": "LOOK AT THE VERA PRODUCT LINE. I purchased this smart things hub to see how it compared - it doesn't. The user interface is so basic it's difficult to use. Want to perform some advanced tasks? You have to go through many screens (phone interface is the only option) picking options and that assumes what you want to accomplish is even possible.\n\nIf you just want to do basic things this is fine but for the same money you can get a fully functional controller like the Vera Edge."}
{"Author": "Trust me, I know...", "Date": "on January 17, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "This + Amazon Dot = EZ mode daily life.", "Text": "My home is officially tied into \"the Matrix\". If you're scared of having to google a few things to get odd things to pair up, it might not be for you, but this this thing makes my whole family's life easier especially since coupling it with our Amazon Dots."}
{"Author": "Visceral Soul", "Date": "on January 17, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I would definitely recommend it.", "Text": "This is my first smarthome hub. I went with Smartthings because it's more of an open platform with a lot of people doing custom development, which means you can find lots of great customizations and tweaks that other people write and offer up for free. So far we only have a Schlage Connect lock hooked up to it, and that has worked flawlessly. I'm looking forward to adding more things to our smart home and I feel confident that Smartthings will let us do that easily and with a lot of features. I would definitely recommend it."}
