{"Author": "D. Smith", "Date": "on December 28, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "The Smart Home Hub to Get...For Now", "Text": "The SmartThings Hub is likely the best hub currently available. That said, Samsung should work hard to continue to evolve the platform as there will likely be many competitors doing the same thing but better soon enough.\n\nSince purchasing, I have become increasingly dependent on this hub as I connect more and more devices. Here are a few ways that I have leveraged the hub so far:\n- flood sensors in basement and near washing machine (IFTTT rule to text/email if water is detected)\n- Lamps - adding phone controlled dimmers, voice controlling with Alexa, auto scheduling\n- Outdoor string lights - voice controlled with alexa\n- Schlage Electronic locks - phone notification when door is unlocked, remotely locking/unlocking with phone, checking battery life, etc... would be nice to manage passwords but not currently supported\n\nPros:\n- Easy to setup hub\n- Easy to setup new devices\n- Easy to integrate with Alexa\n- Fairly dependable/reliable\n- Supports both Z-Wave and Zigbee\n\nCons:\n- The app is not very intuitive, rules are a paint to setup\n- As with most Samsung products, improvements/enhancements are pretty anemic\n- Many devices are still not supported\n- No widget support on Samsung/Android phones (this is shocking!)\n\nTips:\n- Make sure the device is high (e.g. on top of a table) and unobstructed- I had many issues when I kept the hub on a shelf in a bureau\n- Z-wave devices extend the range of your coverage area as they talk to each other, so if you have a switch far from the hub, try to add some connected devices between them\n- I would avoid WeMo devices as they always seem to have issues, stick with Leviton and GE for outlet dimmers\n- Seems to go on sale every few months - wait for a sale"}
{"Author": "Mr. G Galang", "Date": "on December 28, 2016", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "It works with all my smart home devices except the Belkin Wemo Motion sensors", "Text": "It works with all my smart home devices except the Belkin Wemo Motion sensors. Looks like the issue with Wemo Motion has been around since 2014 and it still hasn't been fixed yet (Dec 2016)."}
{"Author": "Wes Z", "Date": "on December 28, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I have had other smart home devices and they have worked well", "Text": "This device is really hard to set up.\nI have had other smart home devices and they have worked well, this one makes it really difficult to configure and personalize.\nOther devices easy to add etc. Still not using this one. Will probably end up being more of a \"dead weight\" device."}
{"Author": "Jesse Cardozo", "Date": "on December 28, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Overall, a solid product", "Text": "I bought this as the first real step towards my smart home and so far it is operating exactly as expected. It integrates with my G-Home and controls the devices connected to it with no problems. It was also very easy to set up.\n\nThe only reason I didn't give this a full five stars is because I had hoped the app would be a little bit better. For example, if you're setting a scene with multiple lights that you wanted to dim to different levels, you can't do that. I imagine that will be an update one day, but for now, it's something to be desired."}
