{"Author": "Frank H", "Date": "on December 27, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great Start", "Text": "This is my first shot at home automation. There was a great sale around thanksgiving and I picked one up. So far I have connected it with three Wemo switches and two GE zwave wall switches, and 3 first alert smoke detectors. It works flawlessly. It also works great with Alexa. One thing to consider, it doesnt not work with Lutron Caseta products, I am ordering a few and going to try and link them via IFTTT. It also doesnt work with MyQ garage door openers, apparently it used to but they cut support, and doesn't work with nest, although Alexa does to a limited extent. Overall I like it. I went with it over wink based on a great sale price and so so review on wink even though it has more support. I think its a great start but just the tip of an expensive iceberg."}
