{"Author": "Jenn", "Date": "on December 27, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "An expensive paperweight", "Text": "The hub has to be within 10 feet of a keypad door to be paired with it, but like most people, my cable internet hub isn't sitting by my front door, it's in my living room. How in the world am I supposed to get the SmartThings hub so close to my front door? Buy a giant ethernet cord that runs halfway across my house, and use an extension cord for power to pair them? Because of this, I haven't been able to use it for my keypad, the only reason I got it. They won't pair because it's too far away. So the SmartThings hub is just sitting in my living room, consuming power, doing nothing but sending me marketing emails due to giving it my information to try to get it to work. Don't buy this unless you can get it within 10 feet of anything you want to pair, with its power and ethernet plugged in."}
