{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on December 12, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "it's not super intuitive and takes some \"exploring\" to understand", "Text": "I purchased this for $50 on sale. True, as most of the reviews say, it's not super intuitive and takes some \"exploring\" to understand, but well worth the time. Once you figure it out, it's simple to add things and create automation. The connection has been rock solid and it works exactly as advertised for me. Worth the $100 dollars, for $50 bucks, it's right up there with the \"Dot\" as one of the best tech purchases you can make."}
