{"Author": "Zach Huett", "Date": "on May 2, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works as expected.", "Text": "Works as expected."}
{"Author": "jabloomf1230", "Date": "on May 2, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Improved - new firmware and software", "Text": "It's not my favorite as home automation gadgets go. Often, it even has trouble finding my Samsung SmartCam, which seems rather odd. I'd pass on this and look at some other comparable options.\n\nUpdate 5/13/2016\n\nThis week the Smarthub received new firmware and the Android app was also upgraded. I'm happy to report that everything finally works as expected. In addition, there is now an Amazon Echo SmartThings hub skill, which allows the use of Alexa with all SmartThings devices."}
{"Author": "Triplebock", "Date": "on May 2, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Works great--lots of home automation possibilities", "Text": "I'll admit that to a certain extent, I didn't need this. It was fun to play with. My wife was more easily convinced than I thought she would be. Now that I've set up the things that I have, though, I think we'd both be disappointed if we lost these capabilities.\n\nI used to use X10 switches for lighting throughout the house. I had a motion/photo sensor aimed out a back window. When it got dark, the sensor would send a signal that would turn on the foyer and front porch lights, so the dog wasn't in the dark and so we could see to open the door and not arrive to a dark porch. But depending on weather or who knows what else, X10 wasn't always strong enough to work throughout the house, and this resulted in hassle.\n\nThe Samsung SmartThings system has worked very well. The mobile application is easy to use. Because SmartThings works with multiple protocols, there is a good variety of controls and sensors to work with, and with more of each, you can do a wider variety of creative programs. Here's what we have done so far:\n* Turn on under-cabinet LEDs in kitchen when motion is sensed in that room.\n* Turn on front porch/foyer/Christmas lights half an hour before sunset (the system can look up when sunset will be that day at your lat/lon)\n* Send text message if water detected in laundry room\n* Send text message when spouses' cell phone arrives home\n* Turn lights on/off randomly during evening hours when we're on vacation\n* Turn off heat/air conditioning (via Ecobee3 thermostat) when French door to deck is open"}
{"Author": "Ken H", "Date": "on May 2, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Two Stars", "Text": "Seems very finicky so far. Many actions fail and you have to retry multiple times until it goes through."}
{"Author": "mwk", "Date": "on May 1, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Save yourself time. DO NOT GET", "Text": "absolutely 100% a complete waste of money and time. Only link 1 zwave plug correctly. NONE of the bulbs i had would link. None. Cree and GE zigbee tried. Went and got a Hue bridge and bulbs to use with the lights and guess what....Hue bridge would not link with the Smartthings HUB. AND the damn smartthings site didn't even see the hub or the one thing i had linked to it. Can't believe Samsung would put their name on this junk. Tomorrow I am sending it back. Terrible."}
{"Author": "David Pangione", "Date": "on May 1, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "MY SAMSUNG SMARtTHINGS SYSTEM - LOVE IT!!!!!!", "Text": "I have \"0\" experience in smarthome connections and installation.\n\nI was back and forth on purchasing the smartthings starter kit + additional items to get started.\n\nI read tons of reviews - many are misleading onhow complicated this system is to set up.\n\nAfter looking around for several months, i purchased the starter set and a bunch of other security items for around the home\n\nAnyone reading these reviews and get cold feet from many of the negative reviews- READ THIS\n\nAfter unpackaging the box / hub, the system was connected in minutes - no complications\n\nI literally inserted the backup batteries in the hub, plugged it in and downloaded the app. The app took no more than 10 minutes between setting up your account and following the steps.\n\nOnce set up, my first device connected in 2-3 minutes ( a wall lamp outlet )\n\nThe system is extremely simple\n\nAs far as the app is concerned, it allows you to break down the entire house by room / device etc.\n\nANother cool item i will mention is that my hub is 2 floors down from my furthest device and works great\n\nI will update this review as i move along but just wanted to put this out there for those reading the many mixed reviews."}
{"Author": "Regina Pellegrino", "Date": "on May 1, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "No good.", "Text": "No good. Does not have programs to support smart code door locks or other items they are claiming yet.\nBetter off with vera if you don't want to pay monthly fees for other programs"}
{"Author": "JS", "Date": "on May 1, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Worked well - so far no issues. There were ...", "Text": "Worked well - so far no issues. There were one or two instances where communication with the hub took a little longer, but overall no major issues with the smarthub.\n\nConfiguring it to get devices working is a little challenging ( did not read manual, just dive straight in :-) ) but manageable. So far only have motion sensor and magnetic sensor - plan on adding switches next month"}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on May 1, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Interfaced easily with Smartthings hub. Responsive to commands from all input devices in our network."}
{"Author": "Derric D.", "Date": "on April 30, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Do Not Purchase", "Text": "I tried for several days to connect this to my current Schlage deadbolts. On Samsungs website it says the locks I have are compatible but on the app they are not listed. I am sorry I purchased this product and wish I would have read the return policy more carefully."}
{"Author": "Robert Shoemaker", "Date": "on April 29, 2016", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Goes down all the time!!", "Text": "Started out working good but a year later it's nothing but one outage after another. Tech support very poor."}
