{"Author": "Terry McHam", "Date": "on March 10, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great so far!", "Text": "I've done a lot of looking before finally deciding to take a chance on this hub. Glad to say that I have been impressed with it so far. Easy to hook up and connect it with most of the devices I already had when I cancelled a lengthy contracted home security service. I like being able to add new sensors and devices as needed."}
{"Author": "Frank Wegerich", "Date": "on March 9, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Pretty cool device", "Text": "Pretty cool device. I moved to this device after playing around with Homeseer and Revolv. Easy to setup if you are technically inclined."}
{"Author": "jam", "Date": "on March 8, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "Product as described"}
{"Author": "Harte Nielson", "Date": "on March 7, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Not Reliable Enough to Run Your Home!", "Text": "This Is a pathetic excuse for a home-automation system from a company as large and as \"innovative\" as Samsung.\n\nI bought this to try and replace my Lutron hub. I loved the idea of SmrtThings' broad set of devices that are compatible with it. I also liked that I could tie in home safety devices (smoke detectors) and home security devices. However, it took very little use to see the very rough edges. I would lose connection to the hub at random times meaning I couldn't check or control and of my devices, timed routines wouldn't run at designated times, and then routines would run at the wrong time.\n\nPlus, the app is absolutely unusable. Read the reviews on the App Store and you can see that it is scathing.\n\nI am glad I returned this before I ended up adding safety devices. With something this unreliable, I can only imagine sirens going off in the middle of the night, random calls going to security companies, and motion sensors randomly turning lights on and off. ** SAMSUNG: SMART HOME DEVICES HAVE TO BE ROCK SOLID!\" Imagine if Google's self-driving cars worked with this level of reliability...."}
{"Author": "Larry Mathis", "Date": "on March 7, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "The hub is working great!"}
{"Author": "JDD", "Date": "on March 6, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Better than the competition", "Text": "Better than the competition, but takes awhile to learn as there is usually more then one way to accomplish a task. Alarm has misfired a couple of times but I think I would buy it again. Several accessories like thermostats and smoke detectors operate just fine without the hub, but it is fun to seek like I'm at the cutting edge of the connected house."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on March 6, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "It works!", "Text": "Perfect out of the box. Great!"}
{"Author": "Bamablueheat", "Date": "on March 5, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Everything you need and then some", "Text": "I have a Piper NV for my security system, it's a great system with just enough automation capability to make me want much more, this ST hub provides every option I could possibly ask for. It's very easy to set up and the app is very user friendly. If you want a very good security system with automation options, get the Piper NV; If you want a home automation hub with some security options, get the Smartthings V2.. I have both and all of my needs are met!"}
