{"Author": "Chriss", "Date": "on March 3, 2016", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I wanted to love it", "Text": "I wanted so badly to love this thing. It does work great......when it works. My biggest complaint right now is the fact that it goes offline for absolutely no reason at all in the middle of the night. I've had the device around 2 weeks and it's gone completely offline twice. A full reboot is necessary. This requires using a pin to push the reset button on the back for several seconds. Those of you who don't have one yet are probably thinking \"that's not THAT big of a deal!\". Well, yes, yes it is. If you are using your hub to control your lights as an alarm clock? It's a problem. If your hub controls your front door lock? It's a problem. If it controls all your lights in general? It's a problem! Shutting off the light switch to these smart bulbs can cause them to lose connectivity and need to be readded to the hub. That's a real hassle. Especially when you have 10 or so fixtures all relying on this technology. I have mine connected to my Amazon Echo and have Alexa turn things on and off. The Echo hasn't lost connectivity a single time. But if the hub is offline, Alexa cannot command any of the connected devices on it's own.\nMy next complaint is the app. Good Lord. I'm an IT professional and this app stresses me out. This is Beta level at best. For a consumer level device, the app should be simple, straightforward, and JUST WORK. Samsung's expectations that anyone who would use/want this technology has ANY familiarity with IFTTT and the like, is just unrealistic. Frankly, when I'm done working for the day, the last thing I want to do is go home and DO MORE WORK! The fact that I've opened 3 support tickets in less than 2 weeks for a CONSUMER DEVICE is obnoxious.\nOn that note. I do have to say their customer service is EXCELLENT. Otherwise, this would be 1 star.\nI'm giving this device until the end of the return policy, but if there's no improvement after that, I'm going to have to go with a different device. Hell, if I'm doing all this work anyway, maybe I'll just built one."}
{"Author": "Mike", "Date": "on March 3, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "love it! the IFTTT integration opens up tons of ...", "Text": "love it! the IFTTT integration opens up tons of possibilities on top of the official supported products. I have this linked with Amazon Echo for voice control that works great, multiple zigbee bulbs, GE 3-way switches, 2Gig 2-way switches and dimmer outlet plug in modules. my only issue is if the internet drops out for long enough (seems to be about 20 minutes), it looses its connection to the cloud and goes offline. Resetting it is easy with the reset button on the back, but when your internet is spotty, that can be something to watch out for. still highly recommend though and will be expanding my system in the next couple of weeks."}
{"Author": "LB", "Date": "on March 2, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Best Smart Hub on the market!", "Text": "These really work as described. I've had very few problems with me and it seems like Smart Things got it right with this. No monthly fees, connect to hundreds of devices. This is really the best gun on the market.\n\nThe first one I had I bricked because I thought the pink lights indicated a problem, so I powered it down. After googling, I found out that I unplugged during an update. It would be a good idea to notate that in the installation instructions."}
{"Author": "Andrew L Peterson", "Date": "on March 2, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Love it", "Text": "Love it, works great"}
{"Author": "Daniel Sayko", "Date": "on March 2, 2016", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "2) The \"Smart Lights\" app is not easy to use", "Text": "By and large, this works fairly well. I have 2 complaints. 1) It forces me to create an account stored in the \"cloud\". I think that's a huge security flaw. 2) The \"Smart Lights\" app is not easy to use. I bought a battery operated dimmer to try to make a 3 way light without having to wire the other side. I didn't have the correct switch yet, so I associated it with a lamp. When I got the switch, it took a great deal to get it to not be associated with the lamp (I had to un-pair and re-pair the switch). I still haven't figured out how to get it to correctly associate with the right switch. I have tried just about every permutation I can think of."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on March 2, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Yes it is pretty easy to use when you get the twist", "Text": "Yes it is pretty easy to use when you get the twist. But for now I just have one dimmer on it and I am very statify ."}
{"Author": "William", "Date": "on March 2, 2016", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "The original hub I received had a manufacturing defect that ...", "Text": "The original hub I received had a manufacturing defect that prevented it from completing setup. I called SmartThings and I have to commend them for OUTSTANDING CUSTOMER SERVICE. They promptly sent a replacement hub and, as an apology gift, an additional sensor for the bother and aggravation. The setup process on the replacement hub went very smoothly and completed in about 10 mins."}
{"Author": "Beard", "Date": "on March 1, 2016", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "So far I love it! I could get lost all day in ...", "Text": "Finally decided to take my house to the next level and go SmartThings! So far I love it! I could get lost all day in the features and Accessories! So far I have 2 portable Outlets, Ive installed 4 way Dimmer Switches(controlled by this Hub), 2 door sensors, a motion sensor and connected it to Philips Hub and Bulbs for further options! Using it all via ECHO and App! No slowing down in sight. Haha!"}
